comment: He's the sweetest, most helpful, brilliant man ever. Take him before he retires forever.

He is a very good teacher and knows his stuff very well. I found it easy to learn and take notes in class. His test are hard, but with studying  your notes and the book, you'll be ok. I passed with a B, and I am no genius in science. Take good notes, and you will be fine. He does curve at the end, and gives you little h/w to help your grade.

Class lectures are boring.  The first test will be hard but gives a big curve.  As long as you study from the notes and the book you can pass the class.  It is a passable class just have to pay close attention in class.

dont take him!!! he's the worst! he makes you be scare that ur going to get an f in his class... he doesnt gives hw so pretty much ur grade depends on ur test grade on top of that he's tests are hard! i failed the class... :(

He's clearly knowledgable about Environmental Science, but he's not very good at delivering the message. His tests are RIDICULOUS. With the course being an elective and not being required for the major program, this man needs to chill out. His classes aren't that bad and you do learn. He talks fast and it's hard to get what he says. Read the book.

The instructor is a fair grader, but he deducts certain points without giving enough feedback. He is very knowledgeable and most of his comments are excellent. He keeps his students interested, updated, and well informed about new policies, deadlines, and class content. Professor McMullin likes rock and he recommends a lot of reading.
Took his class online.  Paper every single week.  You do the readings and the work and you will get a good grade.  If you fall behind you can get into trouble.

I took this class online. Very good professor. There was a lot of reading, and an essay after each BOOK read, but the class itself was very interesting. He helps you whenever you need it, and gives pointers on how to write better essays. You shouldn't get anything less that a B.
I really like this professor, I took his online class and even thought there was ALOT of reading, the assignments aren't bad...just keep up with it and you'll do fine!

I took it online summber B. The class topic (Silk Road) was not interesting but he changes it every semester. The papers are easy and he is very kind and will give you extensions if you need it. Fair grader, I recommend taking only this class during the summer because there is alot of reading, but overall good class.

This class was by far the best writing class that I have had in awhile. I got mostly A´s  in this class and I hadn´t written an essay in five years. There is a lot of reading, but once you have the thesis in mind stick to it and you will be fine. The teachers are very helpful. Take it online!!!

I took this class online recently, and I thought it was quite good! He provides useful comments on all your papers, and the texts for me were pretty interesting (dealing with the Silk Road, Buddhism, Confucius, etc). Of course, as with any online class, you only get as much from it as you put in! I think he graded fairly. Do the reading!!

I dreaded taking this class until I took it with him online.  It is way easy.  I got a 95 on every paper.  There is a 250 word paper once a week and a 1000 word paper every 4 weeks.  There will be a point in time where each week you will be reading a different book, but the essays are 250 words.  Awesome class.  Take online!!!!!!!!!!

World Civilizations -- I was a history hater until a took this class and now I find it interesting. (other class-mates had simmilar feelings) It was A LOT OF WORK - 5 Books to read & write about + lectures. Grading criteria is tough, but fair and consistent.  Class was organized and very well structured. EXTREMELY interesting topics are covered.

Good professor! She likes to embarass people & put them on the spot, demands eye contact & will often burst out at the class for not reading the chapters in advance. But all in all, very easy & stress free class. Just be wise in choosing your partner, make sure it's someone responsible because exams are in pairs. A research paper at the end only

She's a great teacher full of wonderful experiences in teaching, and motivates the students to love what they are going to do "teach".  Not a hard grader at all, and her powerpoint presentations are super easy.  Quisez a breeze, and Phase I, II, & III are a piece of cake with her...easy A.

Very easy class. All you have to do is print out the powerpoint slides so that when you are in class you wont have to copy all the notes down. You have one partner that you do all easy assignments with and the 3 tests with. The tests are based on the powerpoint and some of the book.Efolio paper very easy, she gives you guidelines and easy grader!
She was great. She puts people on the spot but I really learned in this class.

Lectures and Powerpoint are incomprehensible and the book is far more clearer. She is mean and obnoxious and doesn't hesitate to make you look like an ass and feel stupid. She will belittle you as much as possible. No consistency in grading she will grade you what she feels like it. Her instinct is that you are wrong and full of crap.
She was a bit harsh at times, but overall, I had a good experience in her class.

Her class is easy. She might be annoying at times but the class and work is extremely easy. The test are based on Power Point slides that she has on her website and she goes over in class. Grades the efolio really easily.

Very rude! Will make you feel stupid and plays favorites. Constantly reprimands students, which is a bit high schoolish. The tests/quizes are not hard if you study. She is not a tough grader at all when it comes to papers/EFOLIO
confusing and rude. her lectures are good but have nothing to do with her tests.

You can tell that she enjoys what she teaches.  She makes you feel a little stupid if you have a question.  You need to read the book to pass her exams.  There are four exams given in different formats.  The e-folio assignment is a research paper on a topic from the book.  Just make sure that you work on it in advance.

"EYE CONTACT!"  is what she will be yelling for about 70% of class time.  If you look down to write your notes, she will go nuts! This professor is REALLY obnoxious.  Her tests are very difficult.  Her lectures are boring.  I recommend taking the class with someone else.

This was a pretty boring class. The power points were useless, and didn't help your better off reading the text. She's kind of mean, like your back in high school. Doesn't like to see you on the computer wants you always looking at her and paying attention.
No Comments

One of the worst professors I've ever had.  Scatter-brained, talks too much, yells at the good students for the bad ones, constantly interrupts during tests, acts like she's doing you favors when she's really not, and won't listen to arguments about tests.  I was actually looking forward to this class, but now I regret it.
Overall Awesome Professor!!!

SUPER EASY CLASS. Have 2 attempts to do the quiz. then it picks the highest grade, NOT the average. You find the answer in the games and the reading that is given. Textbook not really needed but it helps on some questions on the quiz. 2 exams that is exactly the same questions as the quiz. 5 discussion plus response to classmates. EASY A. must take

Took this class online and its super easy! She gives you the information to read. Quizzes are straight from the readings and PPTs and practice quizzes. Five papers. Exams are made up of quiz questions. Easy A!

I took this class online during the spring 2012 semester. She sets it up as separate modules for each week. There is a quiz on each module every Sunday. It's seriously so easy to follow as long as you check back regularly. She allows you to redo discussions and gives you 2 tries on quizzes. I definitely recommend her. There's no way you can fail.

Doesn't communicate with the students. her class was a mess. Her discussions are impossible grades them very hard. I do not recommend. She doesn't even live in the country so there is no possible way to go meet her in person.

With respect to the online course, this term has been a disaster. Material completely mixed within modules, and instructions stating to study material not on quizes. It is not completely the professor's fault and she has been kind enough to curve our grades. Overall, would recommend this professor. Does not communicate often with students.
Took class online during summer term its easy and you get 2 tries for quizzes.
You can get a good grade on this online class. But too many quizzes and the exams are alright. The only thing is her grading scale, a 90 is a B+ and an 80 is a C.

EASY A! Make sure you do all your quizzes on time because there is no makeup and they account for 20% of your grade! Most exam questions are exactly from the quizzes. I only used the textbook once for one discussion and never opened it again. If you want to take an easy social inquiry make sure you take it with her!

Took her class online. She is great, easy-to-follow syllabus and responds to email quickly. HOWEVER, there are weekly quizzes, but can be taken up to 2x; there are 5 discussions, which require a rather lengthy post and some thought, mid-term and final. Overall, very helpful, but get ready to do some reading and typing for the discussions.

Took the class online. Consisted of 5 discussions, 12 quizzes, and 1 midterm and final. The book is needed to help clarify the online lecture notes. Professor is helpful. She responds quickly to your emails. Overall, it was a pretty easy class. Highly recommended.

Took class online, super easy. 12 quizzes of 10 questions each, you have 20 minutes to take them and you have 2 tries. You can also ask the prof what grade you got in the 1st one so you can fix it for your seconf try. Midterm and final same questions as quizzes. You need the book and the discussions are super easy. Prof responds fast to emails

Amazing teacher. I took her online course and it was so easy! There are only 5 discussions and about 12 quizzes in total. The practice quizzes are similar to the actual quizzes.Theres a midterm and a final too, but they are super easy. Shes so nice, she'll actually respond to your emails promptly if you have questions. I didnt feel overwhelmed.
she is one of the nicest teachers I have ever had! the class is interesting and she always does her best to accommodate to everyone. definitely take this lab!

Took the lab class for 3013L with her, very enthusastic and friendly teacher....easy assignments...know that the main part of this course is 6 field trips that are interesting (if you like the outdoors) but are a far drive..gas money!!  i would take this class again

Even though he is my father he is the most hard working professor. When he helps me out on homework about math and computers based on my IT program he explains to me very well and practices with me and if i don't understand he will gladly explain the method until I fully understand. If you show him that you work hard and practice he will help you!

All I can really say is that he gives no homework to practice the concepts he teaches in class. Though he provides the notes, they are all handwritten and lack clarification so if you miss class and don't annotate them, you WILL be lost. Additionally, his tests get into details which are quite tricky. Finally, remember the Assembly instructions.

A pity professors like him are becoming a dying breed perhaps due to schools unwillingness to hire good ones and most probably because incompetent vultures are lining up to fill their coffers at the expense of the new generation of students not learning much.

Great Professor! Honestly, the material (at first) went over my head, but at the end it all clicked. Go to class & take notes; great lecturer. Hard worker. Try to get your hands on old exams to practice because he doesn't use the book (book not helpful). Curve based on your personal progress.

Great professor, actually cares about the students and always keeps his word. If you can show that you deserve a good grade in his class, he will help you. Dont miss class and TAKE NOTES, exams are from notes. If he says you need to know something, its most likely in the exam.

Very simplistic approach and I gain interest in the subject Answers questions well. Exams are similar to what he covers in class. Very flexible accepting oher ways in solving problems. Great proffessor.
Simply one of the best professors at the Engineering Center. You should not miss class or you will pay the consequences.

A great engineer, an expert researcher, and an experienced educator that cares. You'd better know your logic design and boolean algebra: he will show you how critical that knowledge is! You will design advanced logic circuits and learn algorithms. Think of it as a research class. Also search for material online. NEVER miss class! Read the handouts!
Great Teacher, explains very well and will repeat as much as necessary. Grades on curve. Very fair.
Great teacher, one of the best at the Cpe and EE department....

Seems interested in the subject, but lectures are unorganized and over complicated. Notes he writes on the board are like hieroglyphs. Try to not engage in meaningful dialogue other than questions because he doesn't like that and the responds is usually changing the subject or just ignoring.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Get ready to read--Tough grader

comment: For the first half of the semester I didn't know what was going on/struggled to make the connection between philosophy and biology but after speaking to him and committing to doing the homework and attending class, his study guides, thus test, literally come out of the lecture and minimal at-home readings. He tries to make class fun. A for effort.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Inspirational--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS

comment: He's a good professor, would recommend. This is what you need to do to get an A: READ before class and highlight. Go to class, clear your doubts. Go home and DO the HW, then just repeat those three steps. Before the test, use your highlights to do a review and do the book problems that have answers in the back to check your work. You HAVE to practi
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Respected--Get ready to read

comment: Dr. Hermanson is an understanding prof. However, his lectures are very disorganized. Logic isn't the easiest subject to teach so I can understand. Students talk all class during his lecture, it's very rude on their behalf. But ultimately its why I don't attend anymore and just read the book myself. Homework is mandatory and assigned every class
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Get ready to read--LOTS OF HOMEWORK

comment: I made the mistake of giving this professor a chance and not listening to the reviews people placed here. He is very unprofessional, late most of the time to class, his tests are very hard and on top of that for the final he arrives roughly 45 minutes late, over half the class is gone already. DO NOT TAKE HIM

This guy seems very interested in philosophy and logic and really knows his stuff. Unfortunately, the way he explains things are confusing. He over complicates everything in a disorganized way. You're better off reading the book and studying from there. The material is not that hard, but it's a great class to prepare for the LSATs.

Despite the terrible reviews, I took this class because I needed it. Hermanson isn't as bad as people are saying. His tests are straight from the book and class lectures. If you actually read the book, take notes, and do the study guides you will pass this class. He also posts his notes on blackboard. He tries to make the class interesting.
He is a whatever teacher. He grades hard and takes attendance one in a blue moon and attendance is 10 percent so you need to sit for his boring lectures.
HATED this class. Ridiculously hard for no reason. No leeway on grades. Really hard essay grader. Totally screwed up my GPA. DONT take this class unless you absolutely need it.

Well, this is one of those classes for people who are very willing to work hard. He is a very hard grader but he teaches thinking skills that prove very useful. I got a B in the class and well, I was ok with that because of his harsh grading.

His class is not easy, you have two tests and two papers. He doesn't curve any grades and expects you to understand every philosopher he talks about. When writing his paper, you should always side with his point. I do not recommend him.

If you do not have to take this guy during your college experience, good for you, do not! If you do,I am so sorry! This guy made my life impossible. His homeworks are easy to answer, but he's a knit-picker, and if you write something in a way that he doesn't like it, he takes points off. On my essay, he bloodied it completely. And his lectures: pft

his lectures are great but he tells you conflicting guidelines for papers, tries to avoid discussing what he's looking for, then grades them as if you should read his mind. expects graduate level work for an intro class.  amazing lecturer, but too harsh of a grader. not worth the stress for an intro class, go with a better prof.

I honestly loathe attending his class. His lectures are boring and he really killed some of my interest in philosophy. He knows his stuff but fails at getting his point across. His class is based on 2 papers and 2 exams. It is not a difficult class but he doesn't grade easily. Also, when asking him for help he will never truly answer questions.

Great professor, he grades fairly and really knows and loves philosophy. Makes class interesting. There were 10 assignments with questions about the readings, 3 written non-cumulative exams, and a paper due at the end of the semester. Attendance is not mandatory but he has a sign in sheet because he doesnt want people absent more than half of term

horrible teaching style, never took a professor where i loathed attending class. he speaks to quickly and in this course, focused more on biology than philosophy. he assumes everyone taking this class has a biology background  and if you dont then your pretty much f*ked avoid this class unless you want a biology class rather than a philosophy class
great teacher not easy but very very manageable i recommend him to anyone of average intellect.

Excellent Professor. Has a great teaching style. Really provokes the student's interest. He genuinely knows and loves philosophy. The class does involve a lot of writing (gordon rule) but the topics are great. One of the best professors i've had. The class does involve reading understanding the material, so don't expect to slack though.

Philosophy of Biology. I really enjoyed his teaching style and interest in the subject matter. He is very down to earth and helpful. AND he's coming back from Canada this summer to teach! take him any chance you get. do the assignments and pay attention....not that it's hard, it's an interesting class.

cool guy, very interesting even though he looks like a graduate student more than an actual professor lol. the class is kinda easy to get if you pay attention, im a slacker and i managed to pay attention most of the time and did the h.w (which are not collected but make good practice). theres 5 tests but he drops the lowesst and they're not hard
VERY COOL GUY. MAKES YOU WANT THE CLASS TO LAST LONGER =D
HE IS VERY HELPFUL AND KEEPS CLASS INTERESTING. i ENJOYED IT AND TURNED OUT A GOOD GRADE.

The professor talked with us the entire course, sent us emails to let us know what's upcoming. When you send him emails he always replies in a timely manner. He gives amazing feedback and really lets you know how you can improve on your work.

Awesome professor. I took him online & he was very good about getting back to you when you had questions or concerns. One of the best professors/teachers I have ever had. He gives you enough time to do all your homework and even extra credit. You can tell he loves what you do and his very involved for being a online class. I would  RECOMMEND HIM.

Awesome instructor with a great passion for politics. Gave effective  illustrations during the lecture. It made American Government look so easy. Gave lots of extra credits, respected the students opinions. He was very friendly and always willing to help. If you follow his basic instructions, you can surely make an A. Absolutely recommend him.

Great teacher! He's such a nice guy and really cares about his students learning. Not a hard class even me being a lazy student i managed great grades. I recommend you take him he's one of my favorite.
Extremely passionate about politics. Runs the spectrum of political views. Make sure to read the additional readings!! About 30% of the tests come from these.
This professor was interesting and quite helpful. I learned to think outside the box.

It's just SLS, but he talks about politics which makes class a bit more fun. Generally people don't like taking SLS but I would take it with him, since he talks about more intresting stuff than just bureaucratic SLS garbage. He sends alot of e-mails on current events, too.
This guy goes at lightning speed but I enjoyed the class. Give him a B+
Negatives- too many Books (As others have said) Positives- Learned new things and did not fall asleep.

Seriously, the class seems more difficult than it actually is. Just make sure to go to class becuase he gives 4 pop quizzes throughout the semester, but you can use your notes and the book. I didn't agree with any of his beliefs and contradicted everything he said in the papers and i got an A in the class. All in all its an easy class.
Boring actually, but pretty clever
Not boring that is for sure. haha
His teaching style is not confusing. Mr. Rivero just erases the notes a little too fast. Besides that, he is an excellent instructor as you can tell he pours his passion into the class.

Luckily attendance isnt mandatory BUT his teaching style is very confusing. If you don't agree with his opinions he will not count it right on an exam or a paper. he expects you to buy 3 or 4 books for the semester. BUT! he gave everyone a B or higher, even me and i didnt go to 60% of the classes.
This professor is one of the brightest I have ever had at Florida International University. I love how each book focused on a different IR theory.
Talks somewhat fast. However, he is very smart and the class is super interesting.
Professor Rivero was extremely nice, cute, fun, helpful, and very interesting. I wish he could teach all my classes :)
Best teacher I ever had
Sweet and Knows his stuff!
Very smart! Includes ALL Views!

Nice guy, class is a bit dry, and his views are leftist on most if not all issues. I spoke out in class and in the 2 papers against what he said and covered and I still got an A. If you Read, Study A little, and show up to class it’s easy! 3 Books, 3 quiz, and 2 test. All Easy! Shouting matches? Some can't stand hearing other sides of the issues!

Attend, pay attention, take notes, read the books, and you will not get any lower than a B. Rivero is clear and very involved with the students. He does not tolerate shouting matches and useless time consuming arguments by idiots. I'm sure that the people who gave him bad ratings are those idiots who never kept their mouths shut.
No Comments

THIS GUY IS AN ****.....HE IS A CRAZY TREEHUGGING CHAVEZ/CASTRO COMMUNISTS......STAY AWAY!!!! this is a 2000 level i feel like i'm in graduate class .....he also lowers your grade if you do not agree with him

Honestly, this guy is not that bad. He is very specific with what he wants; however, if you don't like going to class you are going to encounter a problem. He gives random quizzes, BUT he lets you use the notes and the book, so easy A. You have to papers and 2 Tests. He is approachable, so if you need to ask a question, he'll help you out.

Super understanding teacher, very sweet.. I kind of didn't take the final and got a C+ anyway :) Will go out of his way to help you.. his notes on the board just aren't very clear :) go to class and you'll do fine.

This guy is a complete jack ass, he thinks he's teaching a 4000 level course. His assignments are impossible, his lectures are boring and unclear, and he grades really tough. Take this class with another professor. He also assigns 3 incredibly boring books along with boring internet readings. HORRIBLE PROFESSOR! DO NOT TAKE!!

Professor Saltman is pure knowledge. He has 50+ years of social work experience. You would be silly not to ask questions and learn from his experience. He is always available to talk and guide his students. I have taken 3 classes with him and he is someone that I am really going to miss. I am so grateful for our time together!

Saltman is one of the most wisest professors I have ever engaged with. I've heard people say he is too old to be teaching and it's the furthest thing from the truth. His age is what gives him the wisdom to teach and if you engage in his class, you will learn far more than textbook information. I LOVE his classes and I think he's amazing

Professor Saltman is the greatest teacher in the Social Work program, I wish he would teach the entire MSW program. Complete your work, ask for help & clarification when you need it, study for his tests and you will pass. Saltman also makes himself available to students during class break + after class.

Professor Saltman is a great and knowledgeable professor at FIU. He makes social work an exciting profession. Attend class, engage, take notes, read the material and you'll pass this class. This is not the easiest A (he will challenge you) but you're guaranteed to learn something new every time you attend his class!

AVOID HIM! Sits behind the desk and lectures. Has a monotone voice. Needs to retire ASAP. Does not listed to anyones opinon but his own. VERY UNORGANIZED. DOES NOT KNOW HOW TO WORK CANVAS . Gets almost every assisgnment messed up in some way.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Lecture heavy--Tough grader

comment: 'Tangential' is what comes to mind when describing this professor's style. He is highly disorganized and monopolizes the discussions in class. There is little room for any feedback. He's set in his ways and is reluctant to hear a different point of view.

Read the instructions on the syllabus VERY CAREFULLY. He hears EVERYTHING so becareful when speaking outloud. He does not let you out early so be prepared to stay the whole class time. He is an extremely tough grader towards his papers. Hes very knowledgeable, just needs to be approached and his class is extremely disorganized so be warned.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Skip class? You won't pass.--Tough grader

comment: I'm extremely disappointed with this professor. He does not engage the students and sits behind the desk reading off of PowerPoint. I will never take his class again since I didn't learn anything.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--SO MANY PAPERS

comment: It is very clear that Professor Saltman has extensive knowledge and experience in the field and is eager to pass the baton to the next generation. He is a very smart and kind man, with big shoes to fill in the field of social work. His classes are mainly lectures with a few relevant videos, it is important to take notes in order to pass quizzes.

If you have a short attention span, or just don't get his type of humor then you will not like the class. If you give him even half of your attention you will find great insight, amazing anecdotes and knowledge through his extensive experience. Advice for students: pay attention, stay with him when he goes on a tangent; it's worth it, trust me.

Saltman has been in the field for over 50 years. He has tremendous knowledge, experience, and love for the profession. He is aware of his flaws & is not shy about compensating in other ways. If you take time to value his wisdom you will not only do well but will take more than just a grade away from his class. Make no mistake, you will need to work

You can tell that he has an abundant amount of experience and wisdom. Unfortunately, he has been teaching for so many years and it's way beyond his time to let go. He goes on a tangent and lectures from his desk. There's no real involvement. Be very careful when writing his essays and READ THE SYLLABUS VERY CLEARLY ON HIS ASSIGNMENTS.

Professor Saltman is a great and knowledgeable professor at FIU! He makes social work exciting and I look forward to being in the field. Attend class, engage, take notes, read the material and you'll pass this class. This is not the easiest A (he will challenge you) but you're guaranteed to learn something new every time you attend his class!

I do not know why all the negative comments. Professor Saltman is the most knowledgeable Professor on campus. He does NOT keep us in class until the last minute! His lectures are NOT boring. Read the text, slides and you will do well on quizzes. Go to class and be on time! Is that too much to ask?

Prof. Saltman is knowledgeable and passionate about social work. He is one of the few honest and blunt professors we have in FIU. Saltman goes off on rants so prepared to hear him speak the entire class. Attend class, do well on his quizzes, try your best on the assigned papers and you will pass, I promise you! I would take him again.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Skip class? You won't pass.--Hilarious

comment: He has been in the social work field for over 50 years... truth is he needs to retire.  his lectures are long and boring he will keep you in class till the last minute. He is disorganized, and gets off topic for hours. Not a difficult class if you pay attention, but he is so boring that it's hard to pay attention. He is biased when grading papers.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Get ready to read--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: He can be slightly confusing but you just have to ask him for some clarity. SHOW UP TO EVERY LECTURE ON TIME!!! Points will be deducted from your grade if tardy. Took Intro to Social Work with him, pretty easy class and you learn a lot. I would take him again.

His lectures tend to be long and boring, but interesting. He gives good insight to the real world, however his lectures have nothing to do with the readings or what will be on the quiz so be prepared to do the reading on your own. His powerpoints are broad and sometimes confusing but he posts it on BB if you need it. His quizzes are easy, take him!

Professor Saltman is amazing I took him for SOW 5342, 5379L, and  5105. He knows his stuff and is passionate about teaching the next generation of Social Workers. As long as you go to class, participate, and take notes you pass! I bit disorganized but fair. Would take him again and again!

I enjoyed Prof Saltman.  He has a great deal of experience with the elderly and is passionate about the subject.  The class is heavily dialogue driven, which I like. He uses Powerpoints, lecture often went off of them.  If you like a looser format, you'll like his class.  Assignments were interesting. Grading fair.

Do not worry that much about getting a good grade. If this gentleman thinks that you deserve an "A" you will get that grade despite of your poor work. Disorganized, loss his train of thoughts,  a lot of personal biases. Do not recommend him at all.

Saltman is a good professor; however, he is not clear at all about assignments, and if he considers you are a B student you will a B student no matter what you do in class to get a higher grade. Professor can be disorganized at times.
Sweet man. Nice Professor. His class is a bit tough but only because of the subject. He is always willing to help and is very understanding. He is also very knowledgeable. Great Professor.

I took him for policy and hated this class. He doesn't lecture but goes on rants about his opinions. He is not clear about what will be on the quizzes and is very disorganized. I do not recommend him.

He is harsh on papers. There is no specific outline on the papers but is very critical of them. The class is a presentation, a paper, "class dialogues" and a final. Not a big deal. Just make sure to speak up in class as it helps the grade.
I got an A in the class He is very easy to pass. A 5 minute presentation, one exam and a paper.

this professor is unable to speak clearly what he wants on the paper and basically the grade on one paper determines your grade in the class so basically if you write a B- paper no matter what you will be eceiving a B-  in the class which is unfair because of all the othe additional wok that you complete basically is worthless take anyone else
very disorganized.
Great professor, obviously very knowledgeable...but lacks organization and tends to rant off. Therefore might be a little confusing with final class presentation. 3 papers...no midterms or finals!

Professor Saltman is very knowledgeable. His lectures are clear and organized. He is strict in evaluating but if you do the paper in APA and follow his instructions for the class discussions you'll get an A

this is the second class i took with saltman.. he is a bit disorganized but i prefer his teaching style to many other professors. even though he gets off topic sometimes, his lectures are interesting. the assignments/quizzes/papers are not difficult at all... just attend class and pay attention.

In order to understand this class, you must listen. This teacher was on the ground floor of emerging-cutting edge research. He worked alongside Salvatore Minuchin and Jay Haley in founding the building blocks of what social workers refer to as "system's theory."

He is knowledgeable about his subject, however, he is not an organized professor. He is condescending to opinions that do not favor his and will not answer questions thoroughly. He looks annoyed when asking questions and it almost makes it seem like he doesn't want you to ask. No reference of book in lectures, but will quiz. Really disorganized.

Professor Saltman is very hard on papers he will pick your paper apart.  Professor Saltman is very intimadating at times. This class consist of an interview of an elder, 2 dialogs, take home 4 pgs, and a research paper.  Last but not least if he has to not attend class he gives you a paper to write because he was not available! A real hard butt!

The class is easy.  This professor is another story.  He has clear biases and his oppinions are many times the only thing he lectures on. You will never need to open your book. He gets off topic and is vague on projects.  Many others like me would never take him again. if you want an easy grade take him, if you really want in depth learning, dont.
Good teacher and very easy. I recommend to all.

Class is difficult. Professor may be scatter-brained, but she is wonderful. Best to get on her good side (niceness goes a LONG way with her). She wrote me a great recommendation which helped me land a government job. She likes creative examples. Content of paper is very important; google scholar is your friend. Be prepared for in-vivo exercises.
Good professor, but her grading is horrible! I don't think she is fair, and as previously mentioned, she has her favorites (get on her good side). Did not love her lectures!

She is a great professor and  is always concern that her students sre understanding the concept. I had a hard time in the beginning but she makes sure to help if you need clarifications. I can say this professor is the BEST professor FIU has in the social work department. I highly recommend her.

Read the book, do the work, pay attention in class and it's an easy class.  Learned a lot of important information in this class and she made it interesting.   She appreciates students who apply themselves.  She's a great teacher.
Excellent professor - knows her stuff.  Loved the class - fair in her grading.

Good professor very knowledgeable must come to class. Read the textbook. Her quizzes are from the book and can be tricky. The invivos are the majority of the grade so practice and pay attention to her examples. You should pass with a good grade if you follow her directions.

You will be graded on : Quizzes, In Vivos (Skits), and Attendance. She tends to change certain grading things every semester or so. But thus far, If your in class, read the book, and practice what you learn for the skits, you should be fine.

I was so scared before taking this professor because of all the negative comments my friends at school told me about her. However, I can honestly say that this is the best professor I have ever had in my life. She is very strict. You have to go class and always be on time.She is fair when grading. You should always participate and do your homework.

This class was really really interesting. She is so funny and goofy sometimes. Attendeance is a biggie with her, so dont take her if you like to miss class because you will fail. The textbook isnt really needed, well i didnt buy it and never needed it. just do all the work and participate. easy class
This course was a bit challenging. We had a mid-term, final, a grant to write, and homework. Workload was high but the work itself wasn't that difficult.
Class was very interactive. Professor Nan explained material thoroughly. Attendance is mandatory. Professor Nan is helpful and is available by phone or email.

Professor Van Den Bergh, is known for having her favorites. Once your on her bad side, that's it, she is not fair. She is the only professor I have ever had an issue with. Otherwise I have enjoyed all the social work professors at FIU.

Extremely nice and good professor! I had a great experience in her class, i learned a lot of things and i enjoyed her as a teacher. The class is not difficult at all, you just need to take all her notes and prepare from the reviews she gives you before the exams. I recommend her!
she will surprise you with a miscalculated failing grade. The only way to get a fair grade is to keep a log of all your scores. She is very aged and forgetful.
looks can be deceiving
You just have 3 papers and a presentation.  Must go to class everyday.  Really fun class.

I loved this class. This class kind of helped you explore yourself and made you think about your future as a professional. She was very helpful. This was an easy class. The only way someone could have gotten lower than an A- is if they did not follow directions, did not come to class, or just simply did not do the assignments. Did not have an exam.

Professor Van Den Bergh is a great professor.She knows her stuff and she's ready to help out. You do need to do the reading, and if you do you will be okay. There is a big group project that helps you understand the routine life of a social worker, it was an interesting experience. I recommend!

Worst handwriting ever!!! Her tests are a bit hard! She doesn't really review very much. Major group project at the end of semester but it is not hard if you start early. A lot of guest speakers so its good cause she doesn't lecture that much. Very helpful class to learn about social work. Really knows her stuff but a bit crazy!!

VERY nice teacher.  She really wants you to do well.  Study your book and notes for the test. Covers all material well.  Handwriting is hard to read. I really enjoyed her class. Pay attention to grammar on the group project. Class is extremely interactive. Easy class if you attend classes. I would reccomend her to anyone.
A bit hard. She is nice however she grades hard. She even takes points away for absences. Her lectures are fast and her handwriting is hard to understand.

Her class is less focus on exams, do all the HW and come to class, get A's on the group project and do extra credit.. each extra credit is 1% of final grade up 10% try to get B's on the exams and final and with the E.C. you should pass with A also dont get frustrated with exam scores B.C the 5 exams is only 30% of grade and she drops lowest. GL
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--EXTRA CREDIT--GROUP PROJECTS

comment: Nice Teacher, gives extra credit. There's a lot things that are graded so take this class if you're not taking very difficult courses or less than 15 credits
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.--SO MANY PAPERS

comment: Dr. Koptur's class appears to be easy but, given time, one would realize that it requires a steady amount of reading to get an 'A' in the class. The blackboard quizzes demonstrate what you would get on the exams well. Not a big fan of the flipped classroom structure, feels a bit too simplified. Would prefer a lecture environment.

She is a terrible teacher. In class she teaches from powerpoints but the tests are mostly from the book and each test is based on around 10 chapters each. 3 tests total in which the class average is really low ( D class average ) and as of spring 2013 she decided no to curve grades anymore.

Took her Nature Teaching class and it was the easiest class I've ever taken in my entire college career. We would go into the nature preserve and draw trees. Two papers, a group project, and an individual project. Projects had to teach "a 6th grade class." Straight up PIE.

This class was supposed to be an INTRO class and she takes it like if it was an ADVANCED course. The lectures are incredibly boring, she only reads from the powerpoints and she posts them online so there is no point on going to the lecture. There are few assignments, 3 Exams and a final. The exams are VERY difficult, at least 9 chapters each exam.

She is a pretty nice teaher and you dont have to go to class b/c she posts the powerpoint online. had "quizes" in class sometimes that were done in groups though easy grade. It is a nonmajors course but sometimes forgets that. She uses diagrams in her pp but forgets what she's showing, making you more confused than before the class. HUGE curve

This class is for anyone obsessed with plants. I took this class as a non-science major and she basically expected graduate level work. Really boring, study guides are the opposite of exams. She gives huge curves b/c everyone fails. Highly recommend choosing another prof.

she's a very nice lady, but the class is super boring. there's not a lot of hw or classwork and there are 4 tests, one of which she throws out the grade. if you study her power points you should get good grades. also she has a very steep curve.

I took this class for an easy non science life course. Trust me when i say this it's anything but. She is nice, and yes there's not a lot of hw. But we learned a chapter a day. The first test almost everyone failed and the second was whatever. HER STUDY GUIDE DOES NOT HELP! She has a curve, and she's nice. I study for the test, intense.

Easy A.This professor is so laidback that sometimes she puts you to sleep.Her exams are so EASY.She gives in class pop quizzes.But they are already posted on her ppts that she posts a day before on moodle.So look for that.She has a hideous fashion style though.Nonetheless, she is the BEST ecology teacher you can have at FIU.Good luck you guys!

awesome course with her. if you're looking for a very laidback course to take, i strongly recommend taking intro to botany with her. she'd talk to the class as if we were in pre-school, in a very nice nurturing way. it was pretty funny. but its a nice change of pace if your other courses are pretty hardcore.

Nice lady. Class is boring. Easy B, but you have to work like crazy for an A. The volume of work and the pace are ridiculous. Don't get complacent, you have to study or you won't do well. Read and summarize each chapter and know all the details. Tests are not cumulative.

So easy, she basically hands you an A. You need the book only in the sense that all of the material mentioned is in it, but honestly, if you just show up at class and listen to her lecture,  you won't have to look at the book or even review the notes. Her tests are also very easy.

good teacher. very nice! her class is super easy. Just make sure you read the chapters and your good. (ecology is pretty easy to understand anyways. also make sure you practice with the quizzes and flashcards online. they help on the test

ALOT of information given each and EVERY lecture. Very overwhelming. Teaches strictly from powerpoints that she has memorized. Pop quizzes (8 total) totally takes you by surprise. Obscure research paper topics. However,take her if you want a "C". she gives a HUGE curve. Trust me,I failed every exam (50's and 60's). still passed with a C.

Ecology - Not hard but time consuming. For tests do the online practice exams, review the power points, and read the summaries at the end of the chapters. Essays are easy usually the question is posted on the slides so you'll have a heads up. **Pay attention to group presentations she puts questions on exam** She gives the module answers in class.
Don't take this course if you're looking for a bio elective credit. Because the lecture course is 2 credits and not 3 credits, it won't count and you'll have to take another bio elective!!!

She is the worst professor. She doesn't teach,she read off the powerpoint only. Don't get her old exams does not help. The essays, even if you think you got it right answer is wrong for her. you need to be in her own head to know what to write in the exams. She does not help you if you need help. WORST PROFESSOR IN FIU. don't take her.
GREAT SEMINAR TEACHER!!! Presentations require work but she is sooooo nice and helpful!

This professor is not helpful at all, she does not know how to treat a person. She treted everybody in our local flora class really bad with her false smile and her stupid voice, she was really sarcastic the whole time and DOES NOT KNOW HOW TO TREAT A STUDENT. DO NOT TAKE A CLASS WITH HER. She made us go to those stupid field trip without any sense
Class is not hard at all at leat during summer. If you get her old tests U are done. She gives quizes in class which kid of suck but whatever. It is really easy to get an A.Peace.

It is NOT hard.If u read the book, u should do GREAT, but u have to make sure u read everything thoroughly b/c her exams have a LOT of essays/diagrams.I highly recommend taking it in the summer with only a few classes b/c it requires a lot of study time!I'm selling the book for $40.It's about $80 in bookstore!Click on evelope @ left 2 contact ME!

She's very nice but very boring.There plenty of opportunities to do well but the tests are killer! You really must study everything!She does not give reviews for her test and they are multiple choice and essay. This class will defenitely take up alot of your time but you will learn alot.
Nice teacher yet tests are hard.  Only take her if you really have time to invest or already like the subject.

Prof Hunt is adorable. He is really nice prof, he does ppt but he talks a lot and it can be kind of boring. Need the book. Quizzes are really easy and can be online or paper He has a lot of experience on Social Work areas.
He is a nice guy and if you need an easy A, TAKE HIS CLASS!!! He will, however, bore you to death.
I took him for the Policy II class and the previous one and he's the best. Very easy to understand if you go to class and follow his PowerPoint slides. Loved it!

His lectures may be a bit boring at times but he do say a couple of jokes.He is a very sweet individual though.His exams are easy he actually gives you the study guide bank and you just go from there.
Such a boring professor spends half the class talkin about nothing of importance and power points are exactly from the book
nice guy but boring

It is an easy class. he gives you the test questions, and wants to see his students do well. So he will assist you with any questions that you have. the only down side is that his lectures are long...but, hey! he has to teach the class.
She okay. Just be mindful that she will interrupt you during your presentation and make you feel stupid.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Lecture heavy--Tough grader

comment: very rude. belittles the students

She's a great professor! If you don't understand something you can call her or she invites you to her home and you can ask all the questions you have. The readings are dense & everything is important. There is no review. You only need the workbook & her notes. Do the assignments & always text her if you need to cancel do it the night before!!!!!!!!
ratingTags: Get ready to read--TEST HEAVY--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: Dr. Simon's tests can be extremely difficult and rigorous, even if one spends a considerable amount of time studying. Despite this, the class is passable. Dr. Simon is very passionate about audiology and is big on helping everyone as much as she can. She is approachable and provides an out-of-class accessibility that most professors do not.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Although a flexible grader, Dr. Simon's tests are overwhelming. Her lectures are long and she veers off topic. She always says to call or ask for help but makes you feel dumb for it afterwards. She refuses to educate herself on current technology and doesn't use any LMS system (frustrating). Take with caution. Wish we had another AUD prof to take

Thoroughly enjoyed her class. Audiology can seem intimidating at first but she makes it easy to understand. Professor is patient and explains very well. She is there before class and willing to answer all your questions. YOU MUST STUDY! Her exams include everything mentioned in the lecture, no surprise questions and she is a flexible grader.

Took this class in summer. Pain to sit for the 3hrs listening to her many stories & speeding thru 200+ pgs of notes. However, she's very passionate about audiology & you'll learn a lot but for the weekly quizzes, you need to study ALOT in your own time. However she's a very lenient grader, is always available outside of class, & its passable.
ratingTags: ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--GRADED BY FEW THINGS--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: AMAZING teacher. I had no interest in this subject but her love of the field is contagious. She's brilliant and is available to help anyone understand. Can't be in class and NOT ask questions if you don't understand. It's not easy material and you have to be prepared for class and willing to ask questions. Practice audiograms and read her notes.

Dr. Simon is an incredibly smart woman who loves her family and her career however, she isn't a good teacher. She expects us to know everything. She flew through the audiograms, didn't even tell us how she got each number (I had to figure that out on my own). This is the worst course I have ever taken. I rather phonetics any day.

Great class I really learned a lot about audiology especially audio grams.If you don't understand something Dr.Simon will be more than happy to help you in anyway she can.She always makes herself available to her students(love her)You will definitely need to study for the exams. But don't worry she curves and gives extra credit:))

Exams are killer! U dont need the textbook she gives 200+ pages of notes, STUDY THOSE! Used the audiogram workbook. Emphasized to always ask her questions but when u ask her she gives attitude. Flies by notes expecting us to know all the material already. no attendance. no quizzes. 2 optional assignments for EC. study everyday!!!!!!!! (literally)

Dr Simon is a very knowledgeable person, however this class should had been separated at least into two semester classes, IS TOO MUCH! She is not clear when teaching. I wish she could have used more visual aids than so much reading.

Amazing professor, hands down. Only study her notes, the book is never used. Not an easy A; you need to study a few times a week, at least. Don't cram, its TOO much content to memorize. She makes you APPLY the material, hence the lack of easiness. Audiology is pretty tough, but she also gives 15 extra credit points. I got an A.

Incredible teacher! Yes, she give a lot of notes, but basically she just rewrote the whole textbook for you and broke it into smaller sections. She give extra credit in assignments and on the exams. I wish ALL teachers were like her offering not only class time to help, but also any other day like Sundays and her cell/home #. Love her!
She gives over 200 pages of notes. If you study the notes you will get an A. She gives a ridiculous amount of extra credit, allowing ANYONE to pass.

Dr. Simon is truly one of the best professors at Florida International University. She always makes time for her students and will go out of her way to help you out! She is extremely reasonable, knowledgeable, intelligent and well-versed in Audiology. Do your part in this class, study and do the extra credit! I did it & received an A-. She's great!

Excellent professor!  She really gives of her time to help and serve her students.  Driving up to Broward is not that hard, especially, if you really want to learn.  I highly recommend her.  Thank you DR. Simon!

She is nice and knows her stuff.  There is a LOT to study, but she does give you all the notes on a cd, so print them out and add to them in class.  She really wants you to do well, and makes herself available through phone or a study session (but it's in Broward).

If you study the notes, you will get an A. Yes, she offers tutoring in Broward but how many professors will offer to tutor you at 9 AM on a Sunday? She wants everyone to pass and does everything humanly possible to make it happen. If you fail, it's not because she was unfair. She's a wonderful teacher who truly cares.

Teaches material at lightning speed. Says "you got it, right?" "It's easy, right?". No one answers!  Too eager to help on the weekends, pushes students to meet with her all the way up in plantation where she lives for "extra" help.  This is an intro class, all material should be taught in class.

DO NOT BUY THE BOOK ! She teaches everything from a CD that she gives everyone a copy of the first day of class. Do not miss class, you will be sorry. Very nice lady but teaches hap-hazardly, This first test is the easiest, the others, may God be with you. Make study groups, there is ALOT to learn. Get all the help you can, you can never get enough

teri is amazing, so passionate, understanding, and helpful. she is one of the sweetest professors at FIU, and she knows her stuff backwards and forwards. she does so much but still has time to share with her students. she is an inspiration.

YOU NEED TO TAKE THIS WITH MUNOZ!! No exams, big group presentation, and 5-6 page case study paper. She gives you great feedback on your work without penalizing you. She is a sweet heart with an amazing background!!! I wish everyone could take her at some point in their college career.
What an amazing woman! PLEASE TAKE HER CLASS AND NO ONE ELSE, YOU WILL NOT REGRET IT!!!

One of the best at FIU!An inspiration,respectful, motivating, and nice. Makes info easy to understand & very engaging. 2 exams, a pwpt presentation on a topic, a portfolio, and a research paper.At first it may seem overwhelming but turns out very easy.I wish all prof in the SPA dept were like her!

She is a highly intelligent, multi taksing professor. She runs her own private practice, consults in M-DCPS, and is currently getting her PhD with twins and holds a full-time position at FIU. amazing. nice. motivating. You will love her.

She is very knowledgeable and interested in her profession. Gives very interesting details about the subjects covered in class. The class is easy but the tests are not. She expects you to read each chapter and eventually cover the whole book.

She is nice. Is very picky regarding e-folio. You must go to class and be on time. Midterm and final are very important. If you study from book you will be fine. Attend class and participate. Just make sure to do all your work and that you are good at studying from book. Good email communication.

Survery of Communication Disorders. You need the book, but the class is very easy. Very interesting for anyone is Speech/Hearing Sciences. Very orderly. She's super woman, she has a private practice, very involved in the feild, two kids, and still gives a phenomenal class. She makes it very easy to understand. Highly recommended !

Just finished my last exam for the class . It seems that the first test is easy and the 2nd and 3rd tests obviously get harder as you go. I suggest using the CD rom to practice and making note cards to look thru if you have a doubt on one or two questions. Tough class but doable and time consuming. Professor is not bad, he's old school though.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--TEST HEAVY--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: This class requires dedication to reading the chapters, which are lengthy, and helps if you do the practice tests from the CD that comes with the book. Just read the chapters and review the powerpoints to be prepared for the exam. Grades are only three exams. It's not a hard class but is very time-consuming. He's also very knowledgeable and kind.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--TEST HEAVY--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Ok so I started taking this online course with Professor Ardila this Fall Sem. It is Sept & I JUST took my first exam & received 100%. I believe there is a lot of false info. I was really nervous bc most of the comments were very negative BUT the test was straight out of PP's & a lil bit from the book. With a full time job, this is a good class.
ratingTags: Clear grading criteria--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Do not take this professor. Exams had nothing to do with powerpoint lectures. Tests extremely hard.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--TEST HEAVY--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Lectures consist of him just reading off the slides, which are segments and images from the text. No explanation offered. The text isn't necessary to pass the class because the exams are based on the lecture slides, but is informative if you actually wish to learn something.
Lectures are not helpful in understanding material whatsoever.

Very tough class. I think students should have taken phonetics or linguistics before taking this class, maybe the material would have been easier to understand. Memorize those power-points if you don't, that's where the test comes from. 3 exams and about 10 video summaries which helps boost your grade. Got an A. But didn't really learn anything:
Hard class. You have to studyyy! No curves, no homework, no assignments.. ONLY three exams. 1 min per question. Get ready to read!!

Class if based off of three exams, and that's it. The first two exams are easy and straight from the notes, but the third is very difficult, with some questions not even in the book. The material IS very interesting, but I had to CLING to my A. I also had him for SPA 4011, with that class being MUCH easier, getting an A+ in. Great teacher.

Very difficult course. The world of Anatomy was extremely new to me. I figured it wouldn't be that bad, but I was wrong. Power points were all over the place, only three exams determined your final grade and tests were timed based on # of questions. Ex:30 questions..30 minutes. The last exam barely had anything from his powerpoint on it.

Dr. Ardila is one of the greatest professors I have had throughout my training.  His knowledge base and ability to teach me Neuropsychology was excellent.  He knows this field and his passion, as well as his expertise is top notch. I studied under him for my concentration in Neuropsychology while I completed my Psy.D. My sincere thanks. Dr. Bauer

At first, you may be impressed by his credentials and expertise.  However revered he is in the field of brain research, he seems not very interested in teaching.  His tests are inordinately difficult, and he offers no other assignments.  He is intransigent and not open to suggestions.  If you fail his tests you fail his class. End of story!

I have had Dr. Ardila for 2 courses and I find his courses to be highly influential. I do find him hard to understand however, I use his power points and find comprehension much better. His courses are set up to where there is no need for the text. Review his ppt's and all will be good. Also, if you don't get a concept ask him he is very easy going

A prolific researcher.  However,I expected him to be a better facilitator of knowledge. He is unavailable to adequately respond to e mails with learning concerns. His tests are almost impossible to understand and includes material that's not in the syllabus. Got an A, still feel disappointed.

Dr. Ardila's legacy in neuropsychology is cemented and indisputable.  Without a doubt one of the most prolific and accomplished bilingual neuropsychologists alive.  Anyone who has taken a course with him should be grateful and honored.  Be prepared to study hard and struggle with his accent.  Show him your genuine interest and you will do well.

Set students up for failure. Puts things on tests not discussed in class.  Doesn't care about the students. I'm a graduate student, I've had four classes with him and he is always the same, bad!  His English is incomprehensible.  It is difficult if not impossible to understand him.  Without question the worst professor I've ever had.

Had him for an online class and as long as you go over his powerpoints you'll be fine. For the first test I studied from the book but for the second one all I did was go through his powerpoints and got an A. Easy class if you put some time into it. Very fair professor.

He is very attentive, answers emails quickly and his online courses are very complete and thorough. The power point presentations are great. I wouldn't say you don't need the book at all, but it is not used often so get it used if anything. He's also very available to help and writes recommendation letters extremely quickly. :)

I was 1 point away from a B and he gave me a C+, whatever you get is what you get, no curves, no extra credit, NOTHING!! You have 1 min per question, if you go over the time allowed even if you get it correct it marked incorrectly,if it's not completed within that time period. The 1st test is 40 question 40 min, the last 2  are 30 que. 30 min.
All of his online classes are easy if you study the notes. You really don't need the book. You just got to study his notes on Web Ct.

I took the class online and it wasn't that bad though. Make sure to read the chapters if your not the best at science. If you are just keep his notes handy they are very helpful. Great professor although a little hard to understand his powerpoints.

He is an excellent professor, however, due to his heavy spanish accent (and i mean HEAVY) it is hard to understand him. For those readers who speak/understand Spanish, you'll probably excell in all 5 classes he teaches; when the class doesn't understand him, whatever he was attempting to say is said in spanish. Your bad luck if you speak English.

Online, you dont need the book. Three test, all from the notes/online lectures. Read everything throughly you should be fine. He doesnt use a test blocker. Very easy to cheat. Easy A. But beware, he gives no extra credit, no curve, what you get is what you get. I got an 89 and got a B+ just the same. But fair is fair... and thats what he is, fair.

Wouldn't buy the book, he literally outlines each chapter and reads the outline in class. Easy class, but a bit boring because he mostly lectures. You watch around 4 movies and the final is a paper and a PowerPoint which you present, last 3 weeks of class are just presentations. He takes attendance daily. 2 exams, 50 questions each.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Graded by few things

comment: Mitan is really funny and is very interested in what he teaches. You have two exams, and a group project as your final where you present a 5-15 minute performance from a play or broadway ( you can be behind the scenes or act). You also have to attend the plays that are being shown that semester, and write a paper (4-5 pages for an A) on one play.
I plan on taking another course with Professor my Mitan

His lectures are very interesting, he loves what he does and it shows. If you do what you're assigned and pay attention in class you'll do well. You're required to see two plays at the MMC campus, do 1 group performance in class with the group of students you choose, and take three test on what you've learned and seen in class. He also offers EC :)
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Amazing lectures--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: He takes attendance the first two weeks of the semester. Two exams (you better take good notes). No final but there is a group presentation. Very funny, keeps class entertaining. Shows clips of what hes teaching. Dont worry if youre a shy person, the group presentation is for every personality

Really awesome class. Only two exams and a paper on literally anything you want regarding film. One presentation based on the paper you write. If you don't come to class a number of times, it starts affecting your grade, but if you do come, you get like 10-15% extra credit, which is awesome. You watch about 4 movies, all really good.
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.--Hilarious

comment: You dont have to be a Theatre major to love this class. Hes super funny and he gets involved with the class so its easy to learn. Take notes on his lectures and use them to study for the exams!!! Only 1 group project and 1 hw assignment in all semester. Never miss a class and he curves your grade by 15%!!! Wish I could have his class again.

He gave me a C+ because I missed an extra credit attendance when I got in a car accident that day. I showed him the police report he did not care. He gave me a B on the group play, I did not mess up any lines. His test are not easy either my notes were not enough. I couldve made up only 2% credit by ANOTHER play and writing an extra essay.. yeah no
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Skip class? You won't pass.--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: Horrible. Did not provide clear directions for essay. Several questions in the tests were ambiguous. Did not respond to emails in a timely manner. Did not provide feedback for discussions. Mostly graded on 2 Tests, and 2 quizzes. Lectures were short and to the point, but book chapters were 60+ pages. DO NOT TAKE ONLINE.

15% extra credit to your grade for showing up every class is massive. Easy tests based on notes and videos during class. Final project is fun if you have a good group and play to perform. You have to watch FIU's plays, but they are enjoyable.
Easy class! Show up as attendance is a big extra credit boost, you don't use the book, take notes and just study off of that.

I would take him again because he is so funny and made the class awesome!! However, BEWARE the group project and make SURE you guys SET TIME TO ACT TOGETHER for the scene. DO NOT WAIT EVEN IF YOUR GROUP CANT GET TOGETHER. JUST. DO. IT!!!  You NEED TO REVIEW THE BOOK for the 2 exams or use your written notes. Gives extra credit for attendance.
Take his class! 3 quizzes, 1 paper, discussions - super easy just do the work and you will pass. He is extremely understanding!!! Really nice professor!

Wish I could take him again, he is lame funny but bearable! If he teases you he likes you. Attendance is for extra credit, test come from textbook, what he says in class, and short clips shown in class.  Have to attend 2 FIU plays and write a paper on one and a group project that has to be performed.
Danny Mitan is by far the most helpful professor I had. He makes you really get interested in the subject. Great person. Totally recommend him

Amazing professor. He's always cracking jokes and getting everyone in the class involved. Class consists of attending 2 plays, writing 1 paper, 2 exams and a final group acting project. I highly recommend this class it's super fun.

Moves fast with terrible handwriting, so taking notes is almost useless if you want to try digesting material. Read the book and pray. Avoid Yotov or you can.
