If you take her for 1101 or 1102 you'll learn more in one semester in her class than what you did in your entire year on AP English in high school. SHe is a great teacher who truly knows her stuff and cares for her students.

Wonderful Professor, but...Classroom is a NO SLACKER Zone...!! Very Helpful, Makes Herself Available Through Web For 24/7 Access...!! If You Looking For An Easy Way Out...Don't Pick Her...!! If You're Ready For A Challenge...Go For It...!!
She's a great teacher. She's tough and expects a lot from her students, but it's an great class and i definitely recommend it.

Okay so I basicly took her for the nice comments on rate my professor. She is an awesome teacher, really help me improve what I was doing wrong. It is ALOT of work though and she doesn't allow ANY dumb excuses. The class is fun and she MAKES you speak up so you better be ready. If you really want your English to improve then definitely TAKE HER!

AMAZING PROFESSOR!!! You will learn so much in her class! I took her for ENC 1101 and truly regret not taking her for 1102. Her classes are interactive and she'll use everything from paintings, to advertisements, music, interviews, articles, videos, etc to keep the students engage in hte class and class discussion. TAKE HER!

I loved it! First off, being white made me a minority in this class and I loved it. The whole class seemed to join in in my Cuban education. I learned just as much about Fidel as English. As a teacher, she is way too cool for school!!! Asks for more work than other teachers, but still made it fun. Class was awesome, never a dull momoent. TAKE HER

Ms. Natasha is probably one of the coolest college teachers i've ever encountered. She tough with what she wants but does it with a purpose. If you do all the assignments then you'll be fine. All of the homeworks help you with ur essay! The class was fun, No lectures. If you hate BS then you'll love her ... she does not BS at all! i love her class!
If you really want to learn how to write a paper and have a teacher that loves teaching , you have to pick this one. She is really nice and helps you improve on your writing.

I really love this class. She gives a decent amount of homework, but if you do all of them they really help out with the essays. Make sure you stay on top of the assignments, and don't miss class because you'll miss out on important information. She is a fun, energetic, and engaging, but do not take it for granted. Also stay on top of your assignme

Definitey one of the more memorable teacher this semester. She gives quite a bit of homework but its doable. The class itself is alot of fun, very interactive and discussion based. After having 6 other classes with lectures, this is welcome. Oh and she likes circles .........alot.

Favourite teacher of this semester. I have a lot of fun in her class and she is down to earth. She assigns a bit of homework and demands perfection, but it is all reasonable. Won't use the book a lot and the class is interactive with no final. 4 essays tho. Oh and call her Tasha baby. If your reading this tasha, you probably know who it is already
really took time grading papers. definitly looking for conversation in class. good books used to read. great teacher!

This professor is awesome! She does so many things prior to the essay to make you fully understand that concept, and grades easily as long as you dont give a b/s essay!! Trust me she's highly recommended!!

Try looking for other options. This class is SO overated. She is not that bad, I'm not saying you'll love her, but you won't easily hate her either. But make sure to check for homework in the last minute, it will be there even when you have other responsiblities.
Great teacher, gives a lot of help and comments on your essays. Pretty easy if you show up to class and do the work. Highly recommended !
not an easy teacher, gets mad when we make mistakes and makes the class sit in a circle (feels childish)  not recommended for people that don't like writing and analyzing text...

She's great for students who have never been good at English. She taught everything I learned in 9th grade so it was really useless, but if you're looking for an easy class, go for it. She's excessively lenient with her lower-levelled students. I didn't enjoy the class at all.
Amazing professor! Class was easy but I learned so much about my writing from her.
Very good teacher. Easy to pass as long as you do the work.

Prof. Marshall is great, she makes the class fun and you learn a lot. I took her during Summer B, there's work to do and a lot to read, but assignments are super easy, she explains what you need to do in detail, and will answer all emails, super understanding. You can only miss 3 classes.

Nice lady. The class can drag on quite a bit and she goes a bit crazy with the amount of work she gives sometimes. She rambles on a bit more than she has to. The book was pretty much useless. Just make sure you do the work, participate and attend regularly. Its not a difficult class to ace.
Great teacher.
She is awesome! Very understand and super nice!! The class is fun and you learn alot about writing techniques. If you get a chance take this class its AMAZING!!

An exccellent teacher for creative writing, being open to each writer's own style and ideas, allowing students to experiment with the writing for personal growth. She is also considerate and helpful, and she also conducts her class well. Highly recommended.

Amazing teacher! she really wants to bring out the writer in you. i took it during the summer so things went a little fast but she made it so that we didnt feel pressured. She gives amazing feedback on your papers  (take advantage of them!). i dont think anyone who did the work failed. she doesnt impose her own style of writing. likes originality.

The best prof. I've had yet... She really cares about her students and goes out of her way for them.  You just have to make sure you do the work.  She is super nice, but don't take advantage, b/c she won't put up with it.  She is always willing to help you do better. Always available via email or telephone. Super nice. Makes class interesting

Professor Baura is one of the best accounting professors at FIU. He is very passionate about accounting and wants his students to succeed. He makes lectures funny and encourages everyone to study. He provides a lot of materials for you to study. Beware of his pop quizzes. He faithfully loves pop up quizzes. Pay attention to his class !!!
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Inspirational--Beware of pop quizzes

comment: He is very passionate about accounting. He's very funny and energetic but you have to come to class prepared. Class is only once a week so it's impossible for him to cover all of the material in that time. Just show up to class and put in the work.

ACG4101 is a very difficult course, no matter who you take it with. Professor Barua is funny and his classes are not boring but you must teach yourself the work. I barely passed this class and I did every problem in the book twice. It is not easy. Try not to miss classes because there is a quiz each time and you will need those points.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.--Hilarious

comment: Not great man

Good professor, really important to him that the students truly understand the material but you need to read before the class to be able to ask questions. Will definitely attempt to answer every question so that everyone understands but when it comes to lecturing he doesn't teach that  much new information each class.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Get ready to read--Hilarious

comment: Professor Barua is very intelligent but he does not teach. He wants you to study very hard on your own. He only answers questions you have in class instead of going over details in each chapter. When we asked him what to study for the exams he tells you that you need to know everything. If you are very dedicated you can pass this class.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.--Hilarious

comment: Hello you with me? Barua is a cool professor he will keep you awake. Read the book and do the homework if not you will fail. He is funny and makes a ton of jokes don't feel like you're being treated unfairly or discriminated against lol.

He is an awful professor. He won't lecture, he will just ask if you have questions about whatever you read at home, and once you ask the question he will make you look stupid in front of the whole class. I'm a straight A student and I study and read anyway but he is just plain awful, I do not recommend him at all. I wish I had taken another teacher

Great professor. Hard class, but if you read the corresponding chapters before coming to class, you will understand his lectures.  BE READY TO STUDY BY YOURSELF 6 OR MORE HOURS A DAY. It is super hard , but not impossible to pass.

SUMMER CLASS. Super nice, has accent. Taken Summer CQuizzes:15% Midterm:35% Final:50% --regular semester is different. Information is not hard, there are just a lot of things packed into the chapters so you need time to study. He goes over his worksheetspower points in class. We had a quiz every class. Make sure to get the book as backup.

Prof is passionate about accounting. He makes the material easier to understand (not memorize but understand). He is also funny. The only con about prof is that he will not go over all the material. He will answer any questions you have though. Also the material itself requires a lot of time. IT IS EXTREMELY HARD!! Quiz every class, Midterm, Final.

worst professor ever. anyone that says he's great, he probably gave them a grade they didn't deserve. he may know about accounting, but he can't even lecture. makes the accounting school look like a disgrace. very unprofessional

This was the hardest class I have ever taken. The subject is very hard but this professor does not help. He basically acts as a tutor. He does not go over what will be on the test, he says you have to study everything. He shows up late to office hours, gives a quiz every class, and is extremely disorganized. Take any other professor!

Tries scaring students but really wants you to continuously work hard, learn thoroughly & come prepared to class. Best advice: Don't take it personal. He is preparing you for the toughest accounting jobs out there and passing the CPA exam. Regardless of which professor you take, this class in itself  will require 20-30 hours per week of studying.

All the tests are hard but the same for all sections, however what separates Barua from the others is his quizzes. They are HARD,  8 to 10 quizzes worth a total of 10% of your grade and you almost never get more than a 5 in them so it definitely makes it harder to get that B- or B than the others. Read before each class and do exercises from book
He's a great professor, the material is complex regardless. But he makes it fun to learn it. Take him, you wont regret it!

This professor doesn't cover all the material from the book, he's mostly there to answer questions,but his accent makes the class very difficult to understand, plus he presents the information in a disorganized way. He is a though grader. I wouldn't recommend.

I took him this semester and had to drop the course. Attendance is not mandatory but he gives pop quizzes almost every class. His lectures are very confusing and his accent is pretty strong. He does not explain the material well and only goes over some of the things in the chapter. would NOT take him again!

He knows the material but his teaching methodology isn't that good. His accent is a bit tough to understand when he is speaking quickly.   He says that he is a facilitator and not a teacher. The class is tough. They don't play when they say to read the first 4 chapters. If you want to pass do all the problems in the book twice.

The methodology of teaching may appear disorganized and not sophisticated; however, it all comes down to reading  the book and relating to the lectures.  Everything he taught became useful for the CPA and easy to remember thanks to him.

Professor Barua is one of the best professors I've had in my life. He really cares about his students and will explain things 1000 times if necessary until everyone understands. 3 tests, first 2 worth 25%, last one is cumulative 40%, quizzes in class 10%. READ CHAPTER BEFORE SHOWING UP TO CLASS and you will pass.

The only professor worth taking this class with.  He writes the exams so you might as well.  Very smart, very clear.  A little odd, but whatever.  It's a hard class and he wants you to understand the material.  No curve.  You must work very hard!  3 exams weighted 25%, 25%, 40%.  Final is cumulative. Average quizzes 10%.  Good luck!

There is nothing wrong with the professor. Regardless of any professor you take, the class is hard and self taught. But I definitely would recommend choosing him. He is dedicated to the field and has extensive knowledge.

ACG 4101 is the weed picking class. Only the fittest survives, not the smartest. You MUST study and read ahead of lectures. PRACTICE PRACTICE PRACTICE. Do not slack, practice each week and read EVERYTHING. Use connect plus, quizzes are very useful. This professor help make the material interesting and elaborated methods, it's up to you if you pass.

Never in my life have I felt so disrespected by a professor. He wastes a lot of time in class yelling and slamming desks; he’s constantly frustrated that students don’t pay attention even though he doesn’t teach. I am always in the top 10% of my class and I’m very dedicated; this is one professor I highly recommend you to avoid; look elsewhere.
This class is self taught. The professor is just there to provide comic relief. All the tests are the same for all ACG4101 classes. Barua does have an accent but is understandable.
He is the best professor. Is a shame he doesn't teach intermediate accounting 2. It's a hard class, but he makes sure you understand. He is my idol!
This class is super hard but he is the best professor you can have. Extremely helpful

that class is hard. easy to get lost. 3 tests a few quizzes and 1 project. the book is a must for u to understand since he has such a heavy accent. he's nice but i would've taken someone else if i could but he is not that bad.
HE IS AN EXCELLENT PROFESSOR. VERY NICE AND WELL PREPARED. YOU WILL HAVE TO STUDY HARD,BUT YOU WILL LEARN A LOT.

Financial Accounting 1 is not an easy class so don't be fooled. Barua is amazing, he goes through everything in detail and explains it in different ways so that everyone understands. There are quizzes in class which he does not curve in so you should attend. He does however curve on the exams. He is AMAZING. Hands down, best at FIU.

one of the best at FIU! the material is difficult but he is an expert and will do whatever it takes to help you understand. he makes class engaging & interesting. I believe i would not have passed this course with another professor

Best professor at FIU. This class is challenging, especially the exams; you just need to study and not bee lazy. But the professor is awesome! He really knows everything about accounting, and is able to explain the theories and problems very well! He knows the textbook page numbers by heart! Great, great professor!

if u want to have good grades do not take his class. He is a nice guy but the class is hard. THe problem is that there is a difference between the class work and the exams that is given. If u choose his class, just know the material inside and out and hope that you can make it out with a good grade.

This class is very hard and you must study a lot to do well. Prof Barua is an extremely nice professor and will answer any questions you have. Come prepared to class with questions from the assigned problems. Good luck!

Get away from this professor.  He makes jokes about how much he know the textbook.  However, one day tryied to quote the textbook from memory, only to discover that he couldn't.  SNEAKY, DIFFICUL, sometimes OFENSIVE, TRICKY.  Run away from this "professor" if we can call him that.

Best Professor Ever,Extremely detailed, leaves no stone uncovered, Challenges you "Think" and understand the LOGIC behind what you are doing so that you always get it right in life. Class is lively and thought provoking. He knows his material down to the fine print and empowers you as a future accountant to know it as well. Study and EARN your A!

Wonderful professor. The class contains difficult material, but the professor covers it all. He truly cares for his students, is fair, and takes the time to explain anything and everything. You can ask as many questions as you'd like and feel comfortable doing so. There is truly no reason why you should choose a different prof. Very worthwhile.
HE IS THE MAN!

The class was hard.  I didnt like how the prof ran the class.  He gave pop quizzes on material he had covered or some not covered at all. He was a little too loud all the time, and put you on the spot to ask you questions on chapter. You must always be prepared for class. Didnt curve even if entire class did poorly on the tests. Attendance required

Do not take him!false that you will learn from his teachings. This is a hard class so you should study hard and do ALL the exercises of the book. He just explains the power point. He doesnt understand the struggle of the students learning the material bcz you should be already prepared for class for the final study hard No Curve half class failed

Please do not take this professor he teaches only the easy exercises and not the tricky questions and problems of the test.According to him you should know everithing before you go to class. He does not help you invidually He explains thepower point doesn't teach that is not true NO curve for a relly hard class and by DECIMALS YOU WILL NOT pass.

You need to read every single page of the text, including the small letters at the bottom and appendix.  If you work out homework problems, it should be okay.  Instructor is helpful on a one to one basis, but NOT AN EASY CLASS.......
Great, great. You may feel like class is hard... but trust me you have all the resources to do well. Prof is amazing. Best of luck!

extremely difficult class. proff. is frendly. be ready to study, study, study, study...Test are MC but very difficult. class requires a lot of work. I was 1 of the few who got A but wasnt easy at all.
The class is extremely dificult.  The professors not really that nice and isnt willing to help his students much.  DRINK THE TEXTBOOK. The exams are MCQ and a nightmare.  STUDY!!!

If you want to learn than I have no doubt that you should take Prof. Barua for your 4101. He will give you a great foundation for your accounting career. The formula to do well is very easy: read, do more problems than assigned. He truly cares about each and every student.

HE IS VERY NICE AND HE TRIES HIS BEST TO EXPLAINS THE CONCEPTS GOOD; HOWEVER, I HAD A HARD TIME TO UNDERSTAND HIM, AND I HAD TO DROP THE CLASS. I THINK THAT HE HAS A GOOD TECHNIQUE AND IF YOU COULD UNDERSTAND HIM YOU WILL DO GREAT IN THE CLASS.

The material is overwhelming but if you are like me you will pass this class with an A. yes, its posible. just do more that what is require and you will be fine. thats what I did and it work. professor barua is very friendly and he is always open to any question. read before you go to class cause he will ask you questions, he can clearly notices wh

Barua is great! I suggest doing the HW problem for the tests. Even though his exams questions are different, what you learn from the HW problems helps you do well on the exams. You have to study, but Barua loves what he does and is good at it! Great professor to take this class with and he's highly recommended.

Very hard class. Professor is very nice and helpful, but his tests are very hard. He encourages to do homework, but test's questions are very tricky with completely different lay out than in the book.

I don't know why some people mention his accent as a con. This is an accounting class, not an english class. This guy is great in teaching what he knows best - accounting. His powerpoints, handouts and exercises are designed to help you pass with at least a B. I've never had a professor that could teach a hard class so well. Highly recommendable.
I wish I had an open mind for accounting back then. He seemed like a great professor, but I had to drop the course because I couldn't understand what he was saying and I was sitting in the back.

Barua is super funny!  He absolutely loves accounting, which is noted in his teaching.  He is always available to help.  He wants to make sure you understand the material.  He does go a bit fast, though.  I would definitely recommend him.

Excellent prof. Take either Barua or Lin-they are the best! Barua is funny and explains things clearly plus he curves the exams and sometimes quizzes. He really wants you to learn so you can drop by his office anytime. The common exams are pretty challenging though so work hard. With the curve, you'll be fine! Go Barua!!
This professor makes accounting easier that it seems. Excellent,one of the best professors, very helpful, with a great sense of humor. I would even say he is my favorite professor.
excellent!
We are in the process of begging him to teach more accounting classes. WE LOVE HIM !!!!!!

This prof is amazing. If there were more profs like him, less people would quit school. He knows the material that he teaches and he is extremely funny! Willing to always help. Many people want to go to Lin's class but the truth is Barua is also one of FIU's best prof. TAKE HIM! You won't regret it. (coming from a full-time wife, mom and student)
AWEEEESOME teacher! makes accounting fun, he always has your attention, and jokes around in class. HIGHLY RECOMMEND!!!
Great accounting teacher ever!!!!!

Great! If you can't pass accounting with him then you have problems. He explains it to the point a 5th grader would understand it. His tests aren't so bad if you review the study guides. Only thing is you do have to go to class because everything from the test is covered in class. HIGHLY RECOMMEND!

Took him for Fall 06, and I had taken ACG2021 before with no success.  I passed this class with a B+.  I made it a point to study the hand outs and the book completely 3 days before the tests and had success.  This is THE BEST accounting teacher for 2021. HIGHLY RECOMENDED.
This class is hard but he is a great teacher and he is always willing to help you no matter what.

He is probably one of the best accounting teachers i've had. His tests are pretty hard AND long, but if you study and learn at least the materials on the handouts he gives you, you will pass at least with a C. For ACG4101, this class is a great experience.
He is awsome!!! His tests are difficult and long, but if you study you will do just fine. If you study EVERYTHING he tells you to do, you will do exceptionally well!

Great, professor is very clear with all his lectures.  He isn't easy but if you study you can definitely pass his class.  He always sends emails of his office hours as makes himself very accesible to the students.

He is a great professor and explains everything very well. He knows his stuff however, he does have a heavy accent but that is no big deal and you must study for the test because they are not that easy but compared to the rest of the accounting teachers at FIU he is the best, no doubt
Great teacher! Keeps you involved with the worksheets. He is not easy, so effort is required, but an A is attainable. He will go over it a million times, if necessary.

WOW hes an amazing teacher and does everything possible to help you understand and pass the class.... he is great and i would definitely reccomend him.... as a matter of fact i will be taking him for another accounting class
he is a great professor..he funny is always prepared and does everything possibel to help you. just go to class and do the recommended assignments and you will do good

Accounting is no doubt a subject that requires a lot of practice to understand.  If you don't do the practice problems he assigns, then you will struggle in the class.  It is possible to get a good grade if you put time into it.  Barua is a great professor who makes things as simple as they can be.  Go to every class.  His lectures are interesting.
I love Barua! thats all i gotta say
Truthfully he does do alot to help you pass. Like online notes, powerpoint slides, and practice exams. The test are hard, but if you keep up with the class you should be ok.
The best accounting professor. His accent a alittle tough at first and it can be funny. But he is great

This guy is the best accounting prof. Yea he has an accent but once u get the hang of it, you will love it. He makes acct. easy and never lets u forget it.  I had the best time in this class and trust me, if you attend all his lectures, you will do great on the exams. Recommend to everyone.

Probably one of the best accounting profs. Accent is kinda funny, but you quickly get used to it. He is very enthusiastic and knowledgable. Always willing to answer questions, give examples, and re-explain to make sure you understand. He emails you notes for the class. Just show up to class- ACG is still difficult class if you dont work at it!

Good professor, accent takes some getting used to, but teaching methods are effective. Mustttt attend every class everytime if you want to pass because he's pretty fast and it's easy to get lost. Only thing that peeved me was lack of email response time. Failed to respond to a personal problem even though he was fully aware of it.
coolest teacher i've ever had, he's the man, nice fella, with a sweet accent, i dont know what i'll get in his class but he's really cool

Very nice professor. Has an accent, but after a few classes you get used to it. He's very helpful, gives lots of notes, & sends everything through e-mail which is great for study guides. I recommend him!

has trouble speaking english but as the semester goes on it becomes easier to understand can be a little boring but he tries to keep the class involved overall i would recommend much better than some of the other acg profs ive heard will answer any questions you have

Took the course online. Do not recommend this prof.  This prof gives an UNREASONABLE amount of work for a summer course. You can't jam a 16 week semester into a 7 week course. There are quizzes every week. Sometimes 2-3 quizzes in a week in addition to weekly disccussions and assignments all due on the same day.  BEWARE! You have been warned.

The course is not hard but the professor makes it difficult. Assignments are not clear. The books chosen for the course don’t provide much info. If a person needs to contact her  it’s a mission. If you have an emergency, she’s not lenient with deadlines. I would not recommend this professor for PAD3438.
Best class I ever took at FIU.  I learned so much to prepare me for the working world.  The teacher goes over and beyond wants required to help students.  I wish I had taken her sooner.
She is extremely difficult.take her only if you have alot of time on your hands.She gives alot of work and yo must compkete.she does not curve and very understanding.

The worst teacher for an online course. Doesnt care about her students at all- doesnt even bother to answer emails or reply to discussion forum questions. Unrealistic amount of work for a summer online class. most students taking online classes have jobs and a fam but she doesnt care. no flexibility what so ever. no business being a teacher!

I'm sorry but not a good teacher, and def not hot. She cares about her students but she DOESN'T KNOW HOW TO TEACH. The most I learned in this class was how to understand hidden elements in advertisements, and that was because we had a guest speaker that day... but i definitely learned zilch about how to write a good essay.

Yo check this out. I am gonna tell it like it iz. This professor gives extra credit through online wimba, meetings, the whack midterm and final iz challenging. There are a lot of assignemnts and too me she iz a tough grader. I you want to be busy take her and she gives quizzes every week. She grades the onlize assignements but takes time doing so.

As far as online classes go, this would have to be the WORST one bay far! the class structure seems to be geared more towards an "in class" setting vs. an actual online class. the professor comes off as cold and rigid, when asked a question she  cut/paste the syllabus instead of speaking to as a student. too involved for an online not realistic

She is a great teacher. Really cares and her class is a blast. If your english sounds like this "Her class is the worst class and teach I ever took beside Professor Vincent classes. She don't teach or even go any of the assignment and quiz but at least Professor " .....good chance you will not pass. Good chance you wont graduate.
great textbooks! really interesting class. super cool professor really loves what she does
Very clear in her expectations and very fair.  It is a lot of work, but at least you know what to expect from her.  She gives you all the help you need.  Learned a lot.  Highly recommend her!
Very inspirational and super to learn from. A lot of work but she gives eveyone a chance. Down to earth and really gets to know her students. Highly recommended

I took this class online. She gives lots of work so if you're lazy and don't like doing your assignments she is not for you. Quizzes every week most of them are 5 min. Midterm and Final. Oh and plenty of assignments to do. Takes about a month to reply to your e-mail. I would recommend her I got an A-. Make sure to do everything she asks for!
Took the class online, just be ready to take 5 mins quiz, exams can only be taken on a friday.  Assignments are straight forward and be prepared to get everything done on time.

I've taken every class this instructor has offered at FIU. (ENC/CRW/URS). Best prof ever! She'll make you work, but isn't that what the real world is? She really cares about students & wants us to do well in her class and the real world. She's very practical, understanding, fair & humorous. You seriously have to take the best prof FIU has to offer

This class really got me ready for the real world. People who complain about the class or teacher are probably the youngster who don't have a clue on life. I'm a returning student so trust me, she goes out of her way to be fair and just. Since this is a senior level class, students should come ready to do senior level work. Take this professor!!!!

This woman is crazy! She says one thing and does another.  Beware, she gives a lot of work.  Believe me you can do it.  Do not expect to get any help from her.  I made an A in her class, but its because I worked my tail off! BEWARE

She's a nice teacher, but make sure not to get 3 absences or she'll flunk you. There's going to be a lot of writing: 6 poems, 2 stories, and a presentation. You're going to have to peer review your classmates poems/stories. I didn't learn much on the fiction as compared to poetry from her. She tries to help students, but her class was boring.
Requires too much work. You would be better served with another professor for this class.

She is a nice lady but she asks for so much compared to other teachers. you must do a mid term, final, presentation, )is the hardest). you must do not only cover letter, resume and a thank you letter, but also quizes online everyweek. assignments online every quiz, and a blog every week (hard) PLEASE DO NOT TAKE HER!!! you'll do yourself a favor.

She's nice. Seems to be interested in your getting a good grade. I dunno I was bored in the class. If it hadn't have been for the book and some of the videos she shown her calss would've totally bored me. I think her way of teaching/talking is rather boring/unexpressive. She's young, pretty hip, good sense of humor. Cares but u gotta WORK 4 grade!

Very attentive and quickly responded to emails.  This class was fully online.  Assignments were planeed well in advanced and were not overly difficult.  Material was dry but, that's not up to her.  Overall, fantastic.
shes really good no homework!!

Awesome class! Only way you can fail is if you don't follow the rubric. She's extremely fair. Any one who complains about the professor or class must not have done the work. You seriously have the power to get an A or an F. Take this prof.

Down to earth, jokes around a lot but keeps class on track. She is really cool and easy going. She stresses important concepts from the books in class discussions and has students work in groups to peer review. The work is tough but manageable and she is flexible with workload. She does not proofread papers, but encourages visiting Learning Center.

GREAT PROFESSOR! She really knows her stuff and is very helpful. The big assignments are the four papers, but with peer review, the ability to use writing lab/OWL, and asking her for help its almost impossible to fail unless you do ABO****ELY nothing, or skip class. Plus she's pretty laid back and will joke around with you. I wish she taught 1102!
She is Good!!!

Professor Bao is a great professor. I took his online class and and couldnt be more happy! He is very easy, there are weekly quizzes and 2 exams... If you do the quizzes you will pass the exams very easily! I really recomend this proffesor!

Dont be a sheep or hell have you for dinner.

I was interested in going to law school before Vilanova's class. He took that interest and turned it into an obsession. I got an A in the course and learned more in that semester than in the rest of my undergrad career. It is a lot of work, but it pays off because it can all be applied to everyday life. He is the best professor at FIU and a MUST!!!

The most disorganized and unprofessional professor I`ve had at FIU. He`s always late for class, never made a syllabus, and assigned the midterm extremely late. Lectures and assignment instructions are often ad hoc and contradictory.

I am a journalism major and had never taken a law class so I was a bit intimidated at first. The class was super hard but I learned A LOT. Vilanova is a great professor, though unorganized, he really knows his stuff. You need to work to do well though, DO NOT WAIT UNTIL THE END OF THE SEMESTER TO DO A BRIEF. He is a tough grader, but he's brilliant

I love con law and he made this the worst con law class I have taken. He is very disorganized, is almost never on time if he even comes to class, and gives confusing questions/answers and then gets frustrated with the class for not understanding. Its not a difficult class but it is VERY frustrating. I don't recommend taking this class with him.

Took him last spring  for Con Law Powers & got an A. Not an easy teacher but probably the best I've ever had. 2 exams, one on judicial review and another on locating Con Law legal issues and *HOW* it relates to the Constitution. You can't take the final without passing a brief-pass fail,there are plenty. Slackers beware. Laziness not welcome there.

He is not an easy teacher and he forces you to learn. He will call you out in class and ridicule the unprepared, but he is exactly what an intelligent slacker like myself needed to be pushed to learn. He makes me wish I had worked hard enough to have gone to an Ivy league school where I would have had more professors like him. Take the class.

This professor is so good that I dare say that you cannot get a better education in a top Ivy league college that can equate to this brain power! He teaches in a "spatial" way not out of the book but he forces you to think. 1/2 the class dropped by the end of the semester but those of us who held on cannot be prouder! If you try you will not fail.

Great professor but is extremely disorganized! He knows so much about the subject and is entertaining but does not know how balance classes out. Barely any work during the semester but during the last two weeks, he piles on all the work he never gave! Passed with a B by a miracle.

The guy knows his stuff and is very passionate about teaching but he is an absolute DISASTER!!! Our grades weren't even input correctly and we were off syllabus the WHOLE semester.  I'd give him the benefit of the doubt but I did not have a great experience.
HORRIBLE TEACHER!! He will give all the hard assignments for the last 2 weeks of the semester. VERY UNORGANIZED. If you do not like reading a lot do not take him!!

One of the best classes, if not the best, I've ever taken, hands down. Vilanova's passion, level of expertise and charisma are unrivaled. The class consists of one exam and a 25-30 page paper/presentation. Start your research early and the paper will be easy. Don't miss class, take good notes and don't wait until the last minute to do your work.

I took this class with him online. Prepare yourself for a lot of reading and writing. Overall the reading material is easy to understand, and the professor is willing to help, and friendly. But he will challenge you.

if u are considering LAW SCHOOL U MUST TAKE HIM..he may appear a bit intimidating but trust me this man is a caring person.attendance is a must so if u are a lazy person who wants to slack off dont even bother..if u dont read the case u will be left behind. oh he will call on u believe that. his method is great and beneficial. i love this man!!!!!

Although vilanova has an interesting teaching style his grading methods are medieval at best and make no sense sometimes. And he can go on rants and tangents as if his life depended on it. Overall not recommended.

Interesting how my negative review was removed..... I am writing this again because he sucks! I am a good student and got a good grade in his class, but let's be honest, he is the worst teacher at FIU.

A few words of wisdom to get you through the semester: no puedo (he can't stand whats going on), I feel a berrinche coming (he is about to go on a rant), dale nino (words of encouragement after he calls on you, and you start to freak out) and of course- the traffic gods hate me ( he is going to be late)! Best teacher ever CONO!!!!

By far the best professor I've taken at FIU. THE MAN IS BRILLIANT! his teaching style is NOT easy, however, extremely beneficial for the student. He WILL call on you, you MUST read. But the class is great. A MUST FOR ALL LAW STUDENTS. Those who rate him negatively, are those who failed because of their impotence. YOU WILL LOVE HIM!! if you try :)

When he goes on his semester rant about the curve of life and how most of us fall under the 50% average, look at him and smile for he is as much a part of the average curve as you will ever be. Don't be intimated by his vulgar demeanor, he is not running for Miss Congeniality, he is a teacher you are paying, you are the one with ultimate power

If you are a weak student don't take his class. If you don't plan on reading then take someone else. If you are not very bright, take someone else. If you enjoy learning and have a spine take the class and you will enjoy yourself.  You will not be able to bs your way through class. Great instructor, take if you want to go to law school.

He can get under your skin but he recognizes/rewards effort and hard work. He can get a little vague on what he wants, though.  Sometimes you would do an assignment and put 'A' into it and end up with a 'B-' Approach him about this.  This subject is my world so maybe it would be kind of dry if you're looking to simply get a pass grade.

Take this man's law class. If you can't make it, FORGET LAW SCHOOL. You will love him or hate him. Either way, you will have learned something. He is not running a politically correct babysitting service or running for Mr. Congeniality at the Kentucky State Fair. DO THE READING OR PREPARE TO BE SCORCHED BEFORE YOUR PEERS.

guy is awesome! Yes he is offensive, but you have to have a sense of humor. He seems like a jerk that wants to discourage you, but really he pushes you out of your comfort zone for your own good. You will appreciate it later. Atten. not mandatory;  if you go to class- be prepared & do the reading! He uses socratic method & asks questions!

I am appalled at the statements below. He knows his stuff and speaks to students as if they should too. Though confusing at first, after the first few assignments it becomes clear how much you have learned. He does not look at boobies, and he is not here for an easy pay check.. learning is a personal experience.

Horrible teacher. One of the worst at FIU, and that's saying something. Is always late. Doesn't bother apologizing. After all, his time is more important than yours. When he does show up, he is rambling, distracted, unfocused, and incoherent. He's just here for an easy paycheck. Truly sad.

He demands a lot of his students, but that's what college should be. Like multiple choice tests that a monkey can pass? Then don't take his class, you actually have to be prepared by doing the readings and be ready to discuss your viewpoints. If you're delicate and sensitive, you should take someone else. If you like a challenge, he's your guy.

He's not easy, but he is brilliant and an amazing professor. He won't tell you much if you don't come to class prepared but for the most part that is extremely helpful as it actually motivates you to read. Take him!

a lot of reading..makes you try and figure things out for yourself.makes you think which is a good thing boys and girls.will help you if you need it.he does care that you learn the material but if you aren't prepared then he won't bother helping you..if u get offended easily dont take him though..does curse a bit..
Completely concur with the verbal harassment comments made before.  Totally unprofessional demeanor.

Prepare to be verbally harassed and humiliated in front of a group of strangers.  Vilanova is  not your normal FIU professor, he swears like a sailor, and doesnt "spoon feed" you information.  Hes a great professor and can potentially kill your dreams for law school.
Straight up socratic method. Will not spoon feed material,challenging, makes you think...great prof if you do the readings
Straight up socratic method. Will not spoon feed material,challenging, makes you think...great prof if you do the readings
This cat is hardcore Socratic method. If you don't like to read full cases don't bother signing up. In fact if you don't like Vilanova, just drop out now.
No Comments

He is difficult in that he doesn't spoon feed information like other professors, and he LOVES the Socratic method. But he cares about his students and wants you to learn. Oh, and his goal is to make everyone change thier minds about law school. Take him only if you know you will do the work, and there is alot of it!

first part of the course is easy just take very good notes and aim for 100% because the second part of the course is very difficult. He doesn't like it when students ask questions. If the final answer is wrong even if the process is right you get zero.

Talks in a very low tone of voice hard to hear most of the time. Tests are not that hard if you take VERY GOOD NOTES. Tends to get frustrated quickly when asked to many questions he feels he went over already. Recomended VS the other options of teachers for this course!

Shes a good prof online, everything is very clear and doable. You dont need the book, however she used respondus lockdown browser for every 10 minute quiz and tests, so be aware. She isnt a tough grader, but is a bit strict on the work being done on time/no extra credit i believe.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--TEST HEAVY--Would take again

comment: I would recommend this instructor to anyone looking for an easy A. She is very generous with her grading and gives excellent feedback. The course quizzes are very easy, though long, and the assignments are pretty straightforward too. All-in-all, a very good experience.

Easy class. Took it online and I promise you I have not worked for it at all. You have two discussion boards, about 14 quizzes, and 4 exams. All easy and all online. You dont need a textbook at all. She doesn't really help if you want to ask questions but besides that if you need an A take her online.
ratingTags: Clear grading criteria--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: I took this class online and it was okay. You have to read the textbook to pass. The weekly quizzes are based on the reading and it is usually on the small details. Be prepared to read. There is one project and it is not that hard. She typically responds within one day.
She is rude and doesn't care about you or your grade at all. Her secretaries are even ruder. The online class is easy to pass, she's just the problem.

The information is pretty easy, but she sticks to the grading criteria. Don't turn anything in late. She also very degrading to students when you ask her a question., just repeats the syllabus to you. Online classes are convenient to take because you are allowed to tailor the class to you schedule, this class you can't.

It is an easy A but if you do have trouble with something she will not help you at all. She does not care about you grade or show respect toward students. I liked the class but would not recommend her as a teacher.

Good teacher, but must read textbook to receive an A in the class!!  the teacher is caring and he moves at a pace which is understandable. If you "learn and know all material" you will be fine with an easy A, 3 discussion, 2 projects, 13 Quizzes  drop the lower grade 10question , 3 Exam 65 Question . Good Luck.
Amazing class, super easy and fun.   IT was online and a breeze.  Basically took the quizes (10 questions each) and passed blindfolded.  Would definitely take again

I took her for my first nutrition course and first ever semester at FIU (Summer B). It was an EASY A - AS LONG AS YOU READ THE TEXT! Yes, you gotta work at it! The project was fun. I learned a lot. She's always available via email and willing to help. Straight to the point. I took her again this semester for my world nutrition course - Love her!

If you read the textbook thoroughly you will do well on the exams. Took the class online during summer, 6 quizzes, 2 discussion questions, and one project. Read the project carefully it can seem confusing.

DO NOT TAKE THIS PROFESSOR. Pretentious announcements. Pleaded to allow make up and partial credit on (2)assignments missed.This professor ruined my GPA.  I begged her (2) weeks before semester ended.  Explained I am pursuing Nursing school and this would ruin my academic record.  No reply on final (3) e-mails. Missed a "B" grade by 10 points.

Wouldn't recommend this professor. Exams and quizzes are extremely challenging and sometimes unrealistic if you are taking several classes. Very short and rude with email replies as well. Avoid her if you plan on maintaining your GPA in good standing.

Great Professor! Took this class online in the summer. 6 quizzes, 2 discussion questions, and a project. Reading the chapters every week is a MUST in order to pass. Not an easy A but definitely manageable if you dedicate the appropriate time. Highly recommend her!

She is very strict with her syllabus. Don't expect anything from her. No extra Credit & No curves. There are 3 exams, 13 quizzes but drops lowest quiz grade, 2 papers/projects,4 discussions including homepage and survey. It is difficult.Took this online, don't recommend this class if your NOT living in Dade/Broward counties bc of project.Good luck!

This class will challenge you, this class is not an easy A by any means. This professor is Not helpful and Not understanding. She does respond to emails within 24 hours, the only good thing. Quizzes are every week. I don't recommend this professor, you will regret it.

Great Professor! I took this class online during the summer and we have 6 quizzes, two discussions and an essay assignment. If you follow the syllabus you are guaranteed an A! Just read the book and follow her directions!
This is a professor that makes nutrition much harder than what it really should be . The exams are based on Test Banks always using the hardest questions available there.

I dont know how this professor has a happy face on ratemyprofessor. I took nutrition online and it was hard to get an A. We were a group of 5 doing the quizes n test and we worked a lot to end up withB+. You wont be able to know where u make mistakes because she wont tell you. Different quizes for everyone and exams. If u r intrestingim sellingbook
Great class! I took it during the summer and it was fairly easy. Keep up with the readings in the book and you will do great!
she is a great teacher. i took her online for nutrition, she answers her e-mails promptly. Her online tests are easy if you read the chapters. SHE IS REALLY GOOD!!

Took her online.  The course is a breeze so long as you keep up with the assignments, some of which are a guaranteed 100%. Like the person before me said, if you need this class take it with her.  You will not regret it.

IF U NEED THIS CLASS, TAKE IT WITH HER. SHE IS THE BEST AND WILL ALWAYS CARE ABOUT YOUR PROGRESS. HER OUTLINES FOR THE CLASS ARE VERY DETAILED AND THE PROJECT YOU DO IN HER CLASS IS FUN...TAKE HER...BUT YOU NEED TO STUDY AND MEET DEADLINES...I WILL TAKE ANOTHER CLASS WITH HER NEXT SEMESTER UPPER DIVISION

Great teacher and easy class. I took this class online during the summer and got an A. There are 6 quizzes which do require you to read the chapters, but they're not too bad. One project that's fairly easy. All in all, great online class to take. You won't regret it!
Prof. Henseler is very understanding, I was unable to take 2 exams and she let me make them up weeks later. She is excellent and the class is fairly easy.

I took this class online...She is really nice but be prepared because you have to study the material. The quizzes arent that bad and neither are the tests but you HAVE TO STUDY!! There is a quiz every week and the average on them was always about a 7/10. She is a good professor though and really really nice! Also she knows her material really well!

I took this class online. The book is very useful and really sparks in interest in the subject. Prof. Hens. really shows her passion for nutrition and her students. Be sure to make use of her outlines and summaries of the chapters. They're good for quick reviews.

Professor Henseler is AWSOME!! This is a very tough class, but the professors concern and care for each student as an individual makes you want to do good, and you will! I wish all professors at FIU were like Dr. Henseler, life would be alot easier. But, unfortunately not.  Take this class!!!!!!!
The Prof. is just GREAT! The textbook was very good. I enjoyed this class and recommend it all the way!! If you study, you will pass!

I am almost finished this class. I am taking it online. It is not an easy class, but if you read the chapters throughly you will be ok. As for the professor, she is GREAT!! She is concered about her students and responds to emails in no time. I would definitely recommend her as a professor.
Sorry my mistake.  Not HUN3731, but HUN2201

Book is very interesting which makes it easy to remember and understand.You'll get to make a homepage of yourself,take part in group discussion, take quizes based on the chapters read and write a report on your own diet. It is pretty straight foward, it seems that the class averaged had always been about B+ on quizes. Just read and meet deadlines.

Best to take the class with experience with learning the French language. She is a French native and speaks in French a lot, which helps you memorize phrases and understand the language better. Finish online HW by the deadline and pass the tests and you will have an easy A. The key is to practice your speaking every night. "Bonne chance!!!"

Mandatory oral component via webcam on the TA's inflexible schedule and if you can't attend during that time, sucks.  A majority of the grade including tests are from listening to conversations, it doesn't matter if you can read French, you have to understand hearing French. For the credit hours, it's not a lot of work,  but don't procrastinate.
DO YOUR WORK AND YOU WILL PASS. GREAT TEACHER, EXPECTATION ARE ON THE SYLABUS, NO SURPRISES, ITS ALOT OF WORK BUT ITS EASY. I WILL TAKE HER AGAIN FOR FRENCH 2
she is very rude, mean and unapproachable.

This class is not hard if you took french before. The grades are mostly on work book and essays which are not that long. She does count attendance and after a certain amount she takes off from your grade, so go to class. Not a bad teacher, but you need to keep up with your work and study for the test...

SHE'S VERY PASSIONATE ABOUT FRENCH. U DO NEED THE BOOK AND A WORKBBOK FOR HMWK. TAKE A TEST FOR EACH UNIT( TOTAL OF 5 TEST), HMWK, AND 5 COMPOSITIONS FOR EACH UNITE. IT SOUNDS LIKE IT'S ALOT BUT IT REALLY ISN'T.  PLUS SHE LET YOU REVISE YOUR PAPER AFTER SHE MARK IT FOR A FINAL SCORE.

Good Prof! Literature isn't interesting but she always stays fascinated about the readings. Really knowledgeable and easy to get in contact with. She tells you exactly what she wants her papers to consist of. Go to the language lab!

She is such a great professor! Always animated, excited, and oh-so-knowlegeable. Her class is really lots of fun, and I would recommend her 100% Her tests follow her guidelines, and you can expect no surprises. Helps a lot when you're learning such a difficult language. She's a great person in general too! Likes Africa. =)
Great prof
She was awesome. I learned a lot, and enjoy the class. Yes it was a one credit class but you have to do your work and it was very interesting.
The class was kind of interesting but a waste of time and the grading scale was ridiculous. Would not take it if I had a chance for a do over.

I hated her. Completely. She's a terrible professor, she doesn't cover the material properly and has the nerve to grade harshly! She also requires that you blow $20 for Career Services. The final was a 10 page paper, for a one credit class?? Take this class if you want to waste your time. Take aerobics instead, I wish I had.
No Comments
Does not return exams and refuses to explain exam grades.
Terrible grader. Doesnt matter if you write the right answer he will still screw you.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Get ready to read--Tests are tough

comment: Hilarious, best professor.  Uses seating chart to choose who to question to make sure everyone during the year is asked equally (roughly 4 times). Participation based on in class prep and  CALIs and Casebook Quizzes (due periodically, not graded). Final is only grade (1/3 MCQ 2/3 Essay). Have to know the rules to a T bc concepts are intertwined.

Norberg is probably the best first year professor to have. Any question you answer, he will build off of even if it's not really what he was looking for. He cold calls, but you will know if you're going or not because he goes down the row. Always available if you have questions/concerns with the course. I hope to take him again after my first year!

BEST Professor ever! He never lets you feel incompetent or stupid, even if you don't know the answers to his questions. He boosts his students up, and though the subject is difficult, having him as a professor is a privilege and every FIU Law student should take his class. You will never regret it!

He knows every rule in the book & he's willing to help in office hours; his midterm and final are multiple choice and essays but you wont know how you're doing during the semester since he doesn't give grades on the midterm, he waits til he has the final to grade. Stick to the CALI's they are a pain if you wait til the last minute to finish them

One of the best professors I have ever had. Clear, concise,and very knowledgeable. He will not assign something that he will not cover. He is very respectful of his students, and last but not least he is very funny.
Professor Norberg is a great Professor. He makes contracts class as interesting as it is going to get. He is helpful, knowledgeable and available to students. I would take him again.

This man is a machine when it comes to contracts. Extremely on point, clear and concise. He doesn't beat around the bush and isn't afraid to tackle tough questions. And he makes contracts fun, that's a lot more than anyone can ask for. His exam is pretty hard so be on point, also he cold calls so you can get owned any day if you're not prepared.

The best professor I have had so far.  I never thought I would like Contracts, but I just loved going to that class.  He is hilarious, extremely helpful and very precise.  He won't entertain stupid questions or people who love the sound of their own voice.  He gives you a midterm and a final.  Make sure you do ALL the CALI lessons! They are a must

CONTRACTS: Subject is dry as a bone, but he manages to animate the topic as much as possible. Clear, not quite concise, but very good teacher overall. He truly wants to see everyone succeed helpful, and caring about his students. DO THE HOMEWORK and BE PREPARED. Absolutely recommend.
AMAZING professor!!!! He makes things clear! Would recommend his classes to anyone

This professor is incredibly organized, structured, and pedantic; yet he is so relaxed and free-flowing.  Do not let the dichotomy deceive you.  Outline and structure your learning accordingly; be there when reviews are given. The subjects in which he teaches require double the effort; the structure emerges at the end, it is complex and intricate.
Awesome teacher. Really helps the students understand. Must do all homework assignments because he calls on you at random. Also, do all the Cali assignments!

He didn't bust one's arse about things and seemed like a really decent guy.  Helps people out of class...  Not egotistical.  Really a solid prof... so long as you don't have ADD because he isn't going to ride you or entertain you to learn the stuff...
Law School is ****ing hard no matter who teaches the class, but Norberg was cool!!!!!!!

OMG, IN MY ENTIRE EXISTENCE NEVER HAVE I EVER HAD A MATH TEACHER THAT WAS SO GOOD. SHE IS LITERALLY THE BEST MATH PROFESSOR AT FIU AND MIAMI DADE. I HIGHLY RECOMMEND STUDENTS WHO ARE NOT GOOD AT MATH TO TAKE THIS PROFESSOR FOR MAT1033 AND MAC1105

She is by far the best thing that has happened to me! awesome professor very clear very entertaining! If you show up to class you will pass. The test reviews is the key to passing. She goes over the review before every test. Highly recommend shes amazing!
I dont have alot to say about professor Peters. She is just the best math teacher I've had period. Clear, smart, funny, entertaining teacher. Strongly recommend.
First of all, she's pretty.. Second of all, she's smart.. Third of all, she's clear.. What more can you ask for? I got a B because her prettiness distracted me a bit -.-

Wow this lady was amazing! She taught from memory and was always available for extra help. She would give us answers to the reviews and would reopen online quizzes during certain breaks in the semester. If you're not great at math or a slow learner she's the best to teach!

I took her for Trig. The best math teacher at FIU. I highly recommend. Sadly for me other classes got in the way and I could not properly prepare for quizzes etc. I got a C-. She still is a great teacher. There were people in the first day of classes asking if there were openings.
By far the best teacher to take college algebra with. She is the BEST! ENOUGH SAID!

No doubt the best college algebra teacher at FIU. She gives reviews for each exam WITH the answers. She also gave the review that the math department gives for the final exam, and she is the only professor that actually worked on all of them and provided an answer guide. I took the department final and it was easier than I thought. :)
This prof. is cool and very helpful but that may not be enough for college algebra. Her reviews are not always what is on the test and the final was made by the department.....

prof. peters is the best math prof. ive ever taken. FIU should hire more professors like her instead of these other ones who all they do is frustrate you. anyone who can say bad things about faith peters clearly is not human

She's really nice but her test aren't so easy. The final was pretty hard. 1st and 2nd test were easy. 3rd test was the hardest. Finished with a C. Took her for college algebra and got a C too. She's good but not the best. Get a hold of her old test If you can.

I don't know what that person is talking about!  I was in the same class and Prof. Peters never said "that's the way it is".  She always tried to explain the "why" in addition to the "how". She would ask if we had any questions before she moved on. Great professor!

She is GREAT! Shes so down to earth, shes funny, and she doesnt want her students to fail. If you study at all you'll be fine...she gives GREAT reviews before tests, and if you do the review, you should pass. Shes very nice. I would really recommend her if you hate math...I do, and she made it manageable for me. TAKE HER. I strongly recommend.

Great professor! Funny and makes class interesting. Helps with all homework problems (not mandatory) and gives review problems and goes over it the day before the test. Another Plus, she speaks perfect English!

AMAZING! Thats all i have to say. She is by far the most amazing teacher at FIU. wanna know what a true, passion filled actual teacher is? Then take this class. Reviews before each exam. ACTUALLY teaches. Her exams contain only what she teaches shes not like those teachers that will surprise u with things theyve never taught before. TAKE HER!!!
she's the best Math Teacher ever!! and she is extremely hot!!! I Love Her!!! but besides that her teaching methods are crystal clear. You cant fail!!!!
She's awesome. The best math teacher! Her tests are extremely easy if you do the HW and PAY ATTENTION in class. She's the best.

College Algebra is a hard class. This was my second time taking it and she is wayyyy better than my last professor.  She gives a review before each test. The only problem is that the final is made by the department :/. I highly recommend this teacher!!!

if YOU every had problems w/ college algebra... Prof. Peters is ur solution! She is willing to help anyone who has a question. She is super funny and nice. You can't fail with her. (Only if you don't study and don't do the recommended homework) If you dont show up to class, but decide only to show up to the tests, she will kick you out. TAKE HER!!!
BEST COLLEGE ALGEBRA PROFESSOR AT FIU !! take her take her, really. 3 test and a final; gives a study guide before every test and reviews it. truly cares about her students. HIGHLY RECOMMENDED !

Faith is the greatest math professor/teacher I've had. She is amazing. Class consists of 4 tests and she assigns suggestive homework which she reviews before every class. One of only a handful of good algebra teachers at FIU. Must take.

I was so fortunate to have Faith Peters as a teacher. Very helpful and personable. Tests were fair and rendered easy with ample review and helpful, optional homework. If you fear math in any form, take this professor. I cannot praise this teacher enough. Highly recommended.

Excellent professor. Makes learning very fun and makes a tedious and boring subject easy to pass. Do the homework and her reviews and you will get an A. Not even as much work as it sounds. Did I mention she has a good sense of humor too? Excellent professor - recommend everyone takes her class!

Great gal, she's good at what she does and she keeps it interesting, I dont think I've ever had so many laughs in a math class, but dont slack she could only do so much to keep you from failing (she might just give huge extra credit worksheets)!

This teacher is truly nice . Her exams are easy if you study and do you home work on a daily basis, and she gives  in class extra credit quiz's to help boost your grade ( the quizes were super easy) the only thing challenging was the final but a good review is given so if you do that and all the sections there is no reason to get less then B
Awesome Professor. I Recommend her to anyone, her tests are based on her lectures and knows the material very well. Super nice!!
Best math teacher in FIU. Don't think twice about getting her class. You will NOT regret it!!!
best math teacher i've ever had!!! She cares so much about all her students and she really wants you to do good, great at explaining things and she's really funny..TAKE HER SHE'S AWESOME!

She is one of the best math teacher's ever!!!! She makes sure everybody understands the material and she always has a smile on her face. I really learned from her. Her tests arent difficult at all IF YOU STUDY. She gave us two 20 points extra credit to help us boost up our grade. She is the best! Definately a good teacher!! I would recommend her!!

Her class is far more difficult than everyone makes it out to be. I'd say that half of the class I was in either dropped or failed, with very few A's. Yes, she is very good at explaining things, but the material is just far too difficult for that to be of any use. I dropped. Take this class at Dade, much better solution.

She is amazing, she knows the material so well and has such a great way of teaching it. If you attend class and at least try the homework the class is very simple. She is very funny BUT never have your phone out nor be caught on the computer becuase those two things really get her upset... other than that she is awesome! I really recommend her.

Peters' method and personality help all students get interested in the material. She assigns homework that isn't mandatory but goes over it the following class. She makes her own exams, so all questions given are ones you've learned how to solve. She explains how some formulas were created. Also, she's pretty funny so that always helps out.
Aswome teacher. i'm so scared of math as a subject, but she made the cass so understandable.
AWESOME PROFESSOR!  My second time taking this class and she made it SO clear.
